29
00:02:40,075 --> 00:02:42,009
You stay near the truck now.

30
00:02:43,045 --> 00:02:44,979
That doesn't look too bad.

31
00:02:45,047 --> 00:02:47,447
Drop two lines and hold the squad.

32
00:02:47,516 --> 00:02:49,484
Everything I own in the whole world is up there.

33
00:02:49,551 --> 00:02:52,247
All my stuff's up there!

34
00:03:00,495 --> 00:03:03,464
Adcox! Ladder up!

35
00:03:03,532 --> 00:03:05,523
Hey, that's your old man up there, Brian.

36
00:03:29,091 --> 00:03:31,025
Nice grab, Captain!

37
00:03:33,161 --> 00:03:35,857
Take it easy. You'll be okay.

38
00:03:47,381 --> 00:03:49,781
We got it! Come on.

39
00:04:12,173 --> 00:04:13,435
Dad!

40
00:04:13,507 --> 00:04:16,635
Hold on, Adcox. Is that a gas line?

41
00:04:17,411 --> 00:04:19,276
- [Scream]
- Dad!

42
00:05:57,034 --> 00:05:59,434
Hey, Brian! Brian McCaffrey, got some I.D.?

43
00:05:59,503 --> 00:06:02,336
Hey, Willie! I'll give you I.D.!

44
00:06:02,406 --> 00:06:04,374
- The littlest McCaffrey!
- How you doin'?

45
00:06:04,441 --> 00:06:07,706
Hot off the presses, boys! Station assignments!

46
00:06:07,778 --> 00:06:09,746
Hey, McCaffrey! Station assignments!

47
00:06:09,813 --> 00:06:11,906
Why don't you hold onto that for me, huh?

48
00:06:11,982 --> 00:06:14,678
Something wrong with my eyesight?

49
00:06:14,752 --> 00:06:16,686
You really trying this fireman thing again?

50
00:06:16,754 --> 00:06:20,417
- Quitting once wasn't good enough?
- It's in the blood.

51
00:06:20,491 --> 00:06:22,425
- Is that right?
- Willie, you owe me a brew!

52
00:06:22,493 --> 00:06:24,484
Hold on! I'm talking to the fire chief!

53
00:06:24,561 --> 00:06:26,961
Let's look and see what else was in your blood.

54
00:06:27,031 --> 00:06:28,999
I always looked forward to getting these.

55
00:06:29,066 --> 00:06:33,435
- You hold onto those, huh?
- Whoa! I got station 17!

56
00:06:33,504 --> 00:06:38,134
"Aspen Snowmobile Tours. Brian McCaffrey, Sales."

57
00:06:38,208 --> 00:06:40,472
It didn't offer the growth and challenge that I needed.

58
00:06:40,544 --> 00:06:42,273
Uh-huh.

59
00:06:42,346 --> 00:06:44,473
"Cattle Drive Mobile Log Cabins."

60
00:06:44,548 --> 00:06:47,210
- That was in your blood six months?
- The coffee sucked.

61
00:06:47,284 --> 00:06:51,152
"Brian's Sound Spectrum, Direct Hi-end Stereo Sales."

62
00:06:51,221 --> 00:06:53,280
This is your own company. This was a big step, huh?

63
00:06:53,357 --> 00:06:57,794
I was ahead of my time, Willie.

64
00:06:57,861 --> 00:06:59,260
McCaffrey!

65
00:06:59,329 --> 00:07:02,298
What's the matter with you? Aren't you even curious?

66
00:07:04,334 --> 00:07:07,167
Engine 115, right?

67
00:07:12,810 --> 00:07:15,370
How'd you know, you prick? These are supposed to be sealed.

68
00:07:15,446 --> 00:07:17,676
Lucky guess.

69
00:07:17,748 --> 00:07:21,912
And a case of Scotch to the captain at station assignments.

70
00:07:21,985 --> 00:07:23,919
You crooked son-of-a-bitch!

71
00:07:37,734 --> 00:07:39,668
[Alarm Chirp]

72
00:08:03,227 --> 00:08:06,321
[Horn Blast]

73
00:08:06,396 --> 00:08:10,389
[Sirens]

74
00:08:12,703 --> 00:08:14,637
Make us proud, guys!

75
00:08:14,705 --> 00:08:16,639
McCaffrey, that's my cousin's company.

76
00:08:16,707 --> 00:08:18,641
Come on!

77
00:08:18,709 --> 00:08:25,672
[Speaking Lithuanian]

78
00:08:25,749 --> 00:08:28,582
Calm down, Mrs. Vaitkus.

79
00:08:28,652 --> 00:08:32,452
[Speaking Lithuanian]

80
00:08:32,523 --> 00:08:34,923
Mrs. Vaitkus, please, calm down.

81
00:08:34,992 --> 00:08:37,517
[Speaking Lithuanian]

82
00:08:37,594 --> 00:08:39,755
McCaffrey, I think it's a box, or a 211, at least.

83
00:08:39,830 --> 00:08:43,288
- Just give me one minute.
- Hurry, we can't miss this one!

84
00:08:45,502 --> 00:08:47,493
- Hey.
- Hi, Jen.

85
00:08:47,571 --> 00:08:51,029
- I see your grandma's still--
- Yeah, she still hates you.

86
00:08:54,144 --> 00:08:58,080
- You look great.
- Thanks, how long you been in town?

87
00:08:58,148 --> 00:08:59,137
Four months.

88
00:08:59,216 --> 00:09:01,582
- Oh, really.
- But I, uh...

89
00:09:01,652 --> 00:09:03,950
I've been really busy at the academy.

90
00:09:04,021 --> 00:09:06,421
I graduated today.

91
00:09:06,490 --> 00:09:08,515
I can see that.

92
00:09:08,592 --> 00:09:10,651
So what have you been up to?

93
00:09:10,727 --> 00:09:14,424
Well, uh... I work at city hall, actually.

94
00:09:14,498 --> 00:09:18,059
No kidding? That's great!

95
00:09:18,135 --> 00:09:21,366
So... I don't know what--

96
00:09:25,275 --> 00:09:29,507
Maybe you and I could... could get together for a beer.

97
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:31,673
A beer?

98
00:09:33,850 --> 00:09:35,784
Beer... that's--

99
00:09:35,852 --> 00:09:39,185
It's funny. You're acting like I just saw you last week.

100
00:09:39,256 --> 00:09:41,986
When I haven't seen you in what... six years?

101
00:09:44,595 --> 00:09:46,529
You son-of-a-bitch!

102
00:09:46,597 --> 00:09:48,622
Don't want ya overheatin', Brian!

103
00:09:48,699 --> 00:09:50,963
I'll give you overheatin'!

104
00:09:57,641 --> 00:10:00,235
Easy, man. I don't have time for this bullshit.

105
00:10:00,310 --> 00:10:03,143
Well, you've certainly matured.

106
00:10:06,883 --> 00:10:09,716
Well, it's nice to know we can still be friends.

107
00:10:12,789 --> 00:10:16,486
Come on, Brian. We got a fire to go to.

108
00:10:17,861 --> 00:10:20,386
Engine 17, your pressure's fine.

109
00:10:20,464 --> 00:10:22,398
Get out of the way here, please.

110
00:10:22,466 --> 00:10:24,764
Officers, you're standing around with your thumb up your asses.

111
00:10:24,835 --> 00:10:26,769
- Where you going?
- I'm a fireman.

112
00:10:26,837 --> 00:10:28,168
Go!

113
00:10:28,238 --> 00:10:30,729
Whoo-hoo! Whoo-hoo!

114
00:10:30,807 --> 00:10:32,707
Need a second lead-out?

115
00:10:32,776 --> 00:10:34,710
What the fuck are you talking about?

116
00:10:34,778 --> 00:10:36,370
- Get out of here!
- Brian!

117
00:10:39,082 --> 00:10:40,982
This is the real shit, man!

118
00:10:41,051 --> 00:10:42,985
The real thing!

119
00:11:33,437 --> 00:11:35,371
Well, what do we got here?

120
00:11:35,439 --> 00:11:37,373
A fireman's costume, huh?

121
00:11:37,441 --> 00:11:40,171
[Coughing] Where'd you rent it?

122
00:11:40,243 --> 00:11:43,303
Thanks for coming to my graduation today, brother.

123
00:11:43,380 --> 00:11:45,314
You're a real inspiration to me.

124
00:11:45,382 --> 00:11:48,681
I'm sorry, man.

125
00:11:48,752 --> 00:11:53,155
You're really ready to fight fire this time, huh, Brian?

126
00:11:53,223 --> 00:11:55,851
[Chuckle]

127
00:11:55,926 --> 00:11:58,019
It just doesn't work on you, little brother.

128
00:11:58,095 --> 00:12:00,962
- I'll see you around.
- Not likely.

129
00:12:01,031 --> 00:12:04,694
You see, that's where you're wrong already.

130
00:12:04,768 --> 00:12:07,293
I talked to Chief Fitzgerald.

131
00:12:07,371 --> 00:12:10,670
He decided maybe you shouldn't be way on the other side of town...

132
00:12:10,741 --> 00:12:12,675
where I'd never get to see you.

133
00:12:12,743 --> 00:12:14,677
Starting tomorrow, you're going to be...

134
00:12:14,745 --> 00:12:17,680
with the toughest company in the city.

135
00:12:17,748 --> 00:12:20,239
17... my company.

136
00:12:22,686 --> 00:12:25,018
One case of Scotch, Brian?

137
00:12:25,088 --> 00:12:27,579
Man, you're gettin' cheap in your old age.

138
00:12:27,657 --> 00:12:30,956
[Adcox] Get oughta here, girls.

139
00:12:31,027 --> 00:12:36,363
You should learn not to box when the 17's on the job.

140
00:13:05,629 --> 00:13:08,393
Hey, Inspector Rimgale, she's all yours.

141
00:13:25,282 --> 00:13:27,216
Hey, give me a shot of that, will ya?

142
00:13:45,435 --> 00:13:47,426
[Stephen] Hey, Shadow.

143
00:13:47,504 --> 00:13:49,836
So, you gotta cause there?

144
00:13:51,875 --> 00:13:53,880
Mice with matches.

145
00:13:56,950 --> 00:13:58,884
Well, the glory boys are going to have to...

146
00:13:58,952 --> 00:14:01,887
wait a few days on this one.

147
00:14:03,823 --> 00:14:07,259
[Dog Barking]

148
00:14:09,863 --> 00:14:11,330
Sean?

149
00:14:11,397 --> 00:14:12,557
Sean!

150
00:14:14,901 --> 00:14:17,529
Hey, buddy. What's goin' on?

151
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:22,474
It's Uncle Brian.

152
00:14:23,843 --> 00:14:25,777
You'll remember this.

153
00:14:25,845 --> 00:14:27,779
Spinach?

154
00:14:27,847 --> 00:14:31,283
We don't need no stinkin' spinach!

155
00:14:31,351 --> 00:14:33,080
- Mom! Mom!
- Hey...

156
00:14:33,153 --> 00:14:35,314
Hey, what's--

157
00:14:35,388 --> 00:14:37,117
Come here. It's okay.

158
00:14:37,190 --> 00:14:39,988
- Hello?
- Yeah?

159
00:14:41,494 --> 00:14:44,429
- Brian...
- Hey, Helen.

160
00:14:44,497 --> 00:14:46,692
God, I'd about written you off.

161
00:14:46,766 --> 00:14:49,200
I know, well--

162
00:14:49,269 --> 00:14:51,203
So, uh... What's goin' on?

163
00:14:51,271 --> 00:14:53,205
- Can I come in for a second?
- Sure.

164
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:56,131
- How you doin'?
- Okay.

165
00:14:56,209 --> 00:14:58,143
Good to see you.

166
00:14:59,579 --> 00:15:01,479
So that's Sean, huh?

167
00:15:01,548 --> 00:15:03,413
Geez, he's a little giant now.

168
00:15:03,483 --> 00:15:07,783
You'd be surprised what a few years can do to a kid.

169
00:15:07,854 --> 00:15:10,880
- Remember your Uncle Brian?
- No.

170
00:15:10,957 --> 00:15:13,323
You don't remember him?

171
00:15:13,393 --> 00:15:17,523
Hey, Sean-man. Where's your daddy today?

172
00:15:20,967 --> 00:15:24,835
Uh... Stephen's not staying here anymore.

173
00:15:26,839 --> 00:15:29,069
He moved out last April.

174
00:15:32,946 --> 00:15:34,880
Uh... huh.

175
00:15:34,948 --> 00:15:36,973
I'm sorry, Helen, I uh--

176
00:15:37,050 --> 00:15:41,384
You guys should try picking up the phone once in a while.

177
00:15:49,128 --> 00:15:54,395
# [Rock]

178
00:15:54,467 --> 00:15:56,401
Hey!

179
00:15:59,239 --> 00:16:01,036
Hey.

180
00:16:01,107 --> 00:16:05,134
I, uh... talked to Helen.

181
00:16:09,249 --> 00:16:11,683
I thought Dad's boat was finally retired...

182
00:16:11,751 --> 00:16:13,685
to the old family graveyard.

183
00:16:16,122 --> 00:16:18,750
Don't you worry about falling out of this thing?

184
00:16:21,394 --> 00:16:23,328
I've gotta tell you,

185
00:16:23,396 --> 00:16:25,956
I love what you've done with the place.

186
00:16:26,032 --> 00:16:28,193
Yeah, it's comin' along.

187
00:16:33,539 --> 00:16:35,200
You want a beer?

188
00:16:35,275 --> 00:16:37,505
Yeah, why not?

189
00:16:37,577 --> 00:16:40,910
What, you been rippin' off fire stations again?

190
00:16:40,980 --> 00:16:42,914
Just some old stuff...

191
00:16:42,982 --> 00:16:45,542
that Adcox gave me that the department was gonna throw out.

192
00:16:45,618 --> 00:16:48,052
But it's good enough for this tub.

193
00:16:48,121 --> 00:16:49,782
What is this?

194
00:16:49,856 --> 00:16:52,654
"Iron Butterfly," "Cream"?

195
00:16:52,725 --> 00:16:55,489
You gotta be kidding! This isn't an actual operating 8-track!

196
00:16:55,561 --> 00:16:57,495
What do you want, Brian?

197
00:16:57,563 --> 00:16:59,827
What are you doin' here?

198
00:17:03,836 --> 00:17:06,498
I wanna know why you messed with my station assignment.

199
00:17:06,572 --> 00:17:08,870
I mean, does this really have to be...

200
00:17:08,941 --> 00:17:11,375
one of those big brother, little brother...

201
00:17:11,444 --> 00:17:13,969
you broke my G.I. Joe and I'm still pissed games?

202
00:17:14,047 --> 00:17:16,106
Man, how do you do it, huh?

203
00:17:16,182 --> 00:17:18,207
How d'you keep coming up with...

204
00:17:18,284 --> 00:17:20,252
new and amazing ways to fuck up?

205
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:22,254
I mean, that Scotch bullshit?

206
00:17:22,322 --> 00:17:25,655
Am I really supposed to believe you came home...

207
00:17:25,725 --> 00:17:27,920
because you felt heartstrings moan for the family biz?

208
00:17:27,994 --> 00:17:29,928
You were bankrupt! The scary thing is...

209
00:17:29,996 --> 00:17:33,432
you probably coulda got away with it for awhile.

210
00:17:33,499 --> 00:17:35,433
Hang back a little bit at the fires--

211
00:17:35,501 --> 00:17:37,526
You know the drill.

212
00:17:37,603 --> 00:17:40,629
The only problem is, that in this job...

213
00:17:40,707 --> 00:17:42,675
there's just no place to hide.

214
00:17:42,742 --> 00:17:45,677
It's not like having a bad day selling log cabins.

215
00:17:45,745 --> 00:17:48,407
You have a bad day here, somebody dies.

216
00:17:48,481 --> 00:17:51,712
And that's just not fucking good enough.

217
00:17:54,787 --> 00:17:56,721
You know something?

218
00:17:56,789 --> 00:17:58,723
I musta told myself a million times...

219
00:17:58,791 --> 00:18:00,952
I didn't even want to be a damn fireman.

220
00:18:01,027 --> 00:18:03,621
Look, I know I quit the academy before.

221
00:18:03,696 --> 00:18:06,824
- And I know how you musta felt.
- Oh, you do?

222
00:18:06,899 --> 00:18:08,867
You know how I felt?

223
00:18:08,935 --> 00:18:11,369
I gotta do this, Stephen.

224
00:18:13,473 --> 00:18:15,407
I need to know.

225
00:18:15,475 --> 00:18:19,309
Yeah, I think you're going to find out, Brian.

226
00:18:22,181 --> 00:18:25,241
Try not to be late tomorrow, huh?

227
00:18:43,503 --> 00:18:46,700
[Starter Motor]

228
00:18:46,773 --> 00:18:49,606
Give me a break, huh!

229
00:18:51,878 --> 00:18:53,311
[Starter Motor]

230
00:18:53,379 --> 00:18:55,347
Shit!

231
00:18:55,415 --> 00:18:57,349
Come on, damn it!

232
00:19:06,125 --> 00:19:08,719
[Horn Blast]

233
00:19:08,795 --> 00:19:11,263
[Sirens]

234
00:19:11,330 --> 00:19:13,355
Oh, shit!

235
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:17,134
- My car wouldn't start!
- What are you doin', man?

236
00:19:20,540 --> 00:19:22,474
Atta boy!

237
00:19:24,177 --> 00:19:26,111
Damn!

238
00:19:30,383 --> 00:19:32,943
Come on, man. You can make it!

239
00:19:42,395 --> 00:19:45,159
Well, Baby McCaffrey, how you doin'?

240
00:19:45,231 --> 00:19:47,062
How you doin', John?

241
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:50,364
[Horn Blast]

242
00:19:50,436 --> 00:19:52,927
Hey, Axe, you know this rug rat?

243
00:19:53,005 --> 00:19:55,166
Know him? I practically raised him.

244
00:19:55,241 --> 00:19:58,369
He never calls. He never writes.

245
00:19:58,444 --> 00:20:00,412
I'm Brian.

246
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:03,005
I'm sorry.

247
00:20:06,486 --> 00:20:09,319
[Horn Blast, Siren]

248
00:20:17,864 --> 00:20:20,662
All right! Garment factory.

249
00:20:20,733 --> 00:20:24,635
Shake and bake, boys! I think we got a barbecue.

250
00:20:24,704 --> 00:20:28,572
Got yourself a hot one first time out, kid.

251
00:20:28,641 --> 00:20:32,008
[Horn Blast, Siren]

252
00:20:44,957 --> 00:20:47,289
Oh, yeah, this is gonna taste like shit.

253
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:49,828
- All right, let's go!
- Shit!

254
00:20:53,099 --> 00:20:57,229
I hate it when we gotta fucking go look for it.

255
00:20:57,303 --> 00:21:00,238
Call in a box, Otis. We're gonna need some back-up.

256
00:21:00,306 --> 00:21:02,604
Brian, inch-and-a-half.

257
00:21:02,675 --> 00:21:05,235
Get the high-rise jet.

258
00:21:13,619 --> 00:21:17,180
- These moments do try me.
