- All right!

532
00:40:59,047 --> 00:41:02,881
I know I'm gonna have another double... on the hero!

533
00:41:02,951 --> 00:41:05,715
- Give him a hand over here.
- What's this?

534
00:41:05,787 --> 00:41:08,153
Leave 'em alone.

535
00:41:08,223 --> 00:41:10,487
Good job.

536
00:41:11,292 --> 00:41:14,159
# [Irish Jig]

537
00:41:19,801 --> 00:41:21,735
Brian McCaffrey, huh?

538
00:41:21,803 --> 00:41:26,365
Brian, this is my boss, Alderman Swayzak. He wanted to meet you.

539
00:41:26,441 --> 00:41:28,932
You should be proud of helping to save that woman's life.

540
00:41:29,010 --> 00:41:31,979
- That was a hell of a job.
- Don't believe everything you read.

541
00:41:32,047 --> 00:41:35,312
Don't be so modest, Brian.

542
00:41:35,383 --> 00:41:37,874
See that?

543
00:41:37,952 --> 00:41:40,546
That's a mannequin.

544
00:41:51,232 --> 00:41:53,166
Look, Brian,

545
00:41:53,234 --> 00:41:56,601
let me just get down to it, okay?

546
00:41:56,671 --> 00:42:00,232
I've been checking you out. Jennifer can't say enough.

547
00:42:02,844 --> 00:42:04,971
I need your help.

548
00:42:05,046 --> 00:42:08,345
- I'm gonna offer you a job.
- I've already got a job.

549
00:42:08,416 --> 00:42:11,579
The great thing about this job, it's still with the fire department.

550
00:42:11,653 --> 00:42:15,248
One of your best investigators, Don Rimgale, is working a really tough case.

551
00:42:15,323 --> 00:42:17,757
He needs an extra pair of hands.

552
00:42:17,826 --> 00:42:20,454
If that name is gonna come from my office,

553
00:42:20,528 --> 00:42:22,723
- I want it to be you.
- Why is that?

554
00:42:22,797 --> 00:42:27,166
I want someone from a real traditional fire-fighting clan.

555
00:42:27,235 --> 00:42:30,727
Yeah, we got all kinds of traditions...

556
00:42:30,805 --> 00:42:33,706
like dying young. Thanks anyway.

557
00:42:39,747 --> 00:42:44,377
Took you all of 30 seconds to blow that off.

558
00:42:44,452 --> 00:42:48,582
Brian, I know it's not my place to say this,

559
00:42:48,656 --> 00:42:52,490
but I think you're passing on a great opportunity.

560
00:42:52,560 --> 00:42:56,223
- You're smarter than that.
- Look, Jen.

561
00:42:56,297 --> 00:43:00,631
I'm trying to do something here. Can't you see that?

562
00:43:00,702 --> 00:43:02,932
I'm trying to be a fireman,

563
00:43:03,004 --> 00:43:05,598
not some kind of poster boy for Swayzak.

564
00:43:05,673 --> 00:43:08,836
There's gotta be at least 500 other smoke eaters here...

565
00:43:08,910 --> 00:43:11,743
that do that shit for real every day.

566
00:43:11,813 --> 00:43:15,010
Why don't you tell Swayzak to talk to one of them?

567
00:43:35,870 --> 00:43:40,034
#Lost the wanted driver#

568
00:43:42,844 --> 00:43:48,441
#His crooked style forgotten and unchanged#

569
00:43:51,119 --> 00:43:55,715
#He took a train to draw me over#

570
00:43:57,959 --> 00:44:00,325
#You're not the only one#

571
00:44:00,395 --> 00:44:05,025
#Caught where there's nothing for you#

572
00:44:05,099 --> 00:44:07,158
[Grindle] Hey, Bull, slow down.

573
00:44:07,235 --> 00:44:10,762
#I used to be king of the evening#

574
00:44:10,838 --> 00:44:14,968
#And I'm not ungenerous now#

575
00:44:15,043 --> 00:44:17,637
#The work is light but not easy#

576
00:44:17,712 --> 00:44:20,078
Helen, can I talk to you for a minute?

577
00:44:20,148 --> 00:44:23,276
- What about?
- It's about Sean.

578
00:44:23,351 --> 00:44:26,650
Right here, right now, you wanna talk about Sean?

579
00:44:26,721 --> 00:44:29,281
- How you doin', Stephen?
- Hey, Jackson.

580
00:44:29,357 --> 00:44:32,656
You don't have to stop dancing.

581
00:44:32,727 --> 00:44:35,696
It's only our son, for Christ's sake.

582
00:44:35,763 --> 00:44:38,789
- Stephen, you don't have to remind me.
- Stephen,

583
00:44:38,866 --> 00:44:43,462
- what about your dumbass brother?
- Wait a second.

584
00:44:43,538 --> 00:44:47,975
Saving a mannequin. How fuckin' stupid can a guy get?

585
00:44:48,042 --> 00:44:51,136
- Stephen, relax.
- Let go.

586
00:44:53,214 --> 00:44:55,444
Stephen!

587
00:44:55,516 --> 00:44:58,974
You got anything else you want to say about my brother?

588
00:44:59,053 --> 00:45:01,487
Goddamn you, McCaffrey!

589
00:45:07,095 --> 00:45:10,064
Atta boy, Brian!

590
00:45:13,334 --> 00:45:15,302
Take it outside!

591
00:45:15,370 --> 00:45:19,204
- Knock it off!
- Come here, you son-of-a-bitch!

592
00:45:21,643 --> 00:45:24,441
Ow-ow-ow. Oh, I'm bleeding.

593
00:45:27,515 --> 00:45:29,813
Jesus!

594
00:45:29,884 --> 00:45:32,409
Knock it off. Come on, eh?

595
00:45:32,487 --> 00:45:34,614
Hey! Knock it off.

596
00:45:34,689 --> 00:45:37,590
Hey, hey, I'm fine.

597
00:45:37,659 --> 00:45:40,219
Jesus, Stevie, you never know when to quit, do you?

598
00:45:40,295 --> 00:45:42,320
Do you ever wonder why...

599
00:45:42,397 --> 00:45:46,299
you're stuck a fucking lieutenant for life?

600
00:45:46,367 --> 00:45:48,631
No.

601
00:45:55,543 --> 00:45:57,807
Come on. Let's get a drink.

602
00:45:57,879 --> 00:46:00,109
- [Brian] You okay?
- Yeah, I'm all right.

603
00:46:00,181 --> 00:46:02,081
Hey, whoa!

604
00:46:03,418 --> 00:46:06,979
- Get him outta here!
- I just wanna get a drink.

605
00:46:07,055 --> 00:46:10,684
You need to get the hell outta here. Let's go.

606
00:46:10,758 --> 00:46:13,278
The whole family's crazy.

607
00:46:13,411 --> 00:46:15,777
[Brian] You nailed him.

608
00:46:15,847 --> 00:46:17,872
He's all right. He said something.

609
00:46:17,949 --> 00:46:20,577
- What'd he say?
- I don't remember.

610
00:46:20,652 --> 00:46:22,677
Listen, I can walk by myself.

611
00:46:22,754 --> 00:46:25,552
Ow! I hurt my ankle, man.

612
00:46:25,624 --> 00:46:28,957
Don't stand and laugh. Get me up!

613
00:46:29,027 --> 00:46:32,895
Yeah. Oop. Photographer.

614
00:46:32,964 --> 00:46:36,400
- Think I can get on the cover of "Life"?
- Let's go.

615
00:46:36,468 --> 00:46:38,959
- Is Axe a great guy?
- Huh?

616
00:46:39,037 --> 00:46:42,131
He doesn't know shit about what I want.

617
00:46:42,207 --> 00:46:44,903
[Stephen] I've got news for everybody. I'm not my old man.

618
00:46:44,976 --> 00:46:49,845
A fire won't get me. I know more than he did.

619
00:46:49,915 --> 00:46:52,884
I know more about fire than all of 'em.

620
00:46:52,951 --> 00:46:56,148
Time for bed, Sugar Ray.

621
00:46:56,221 --> 00:46:58,246
Let me get those for you.

622
00:46:58,323 --> 00:47:00,621
Get outta my way. I can get my shoes off.

623
00:47:00,692 --> 00:47:03,627
You're such a pain in the ass.

624
00:47:03,695 --> 00:47:05,959
You always were.

625
00:47:06,031 --> 00:47:09,967
What are you talkin' about? I saved your ass tonight.

626
00:47:13,305 --> 00:47:17,605
Why don't they trust me anymore, huh, Brian?

627
00:47:17,676 --> 00:47:22,613
Really, the guys just don't trust me anymore.

628
00:47:32,190 --> 00:47:36,718
Hey, this boat could be great, don't you think?

629
00:47:39,264 --> 00:47:41,357
Maybe I'll just...

630
00:47:44,269 --> 00:47:48,069
just take it out on weekends.

631
00:47:49,140 --> 00:47:52,871
Sean and me.

632
00:47:52,944 --> 00:47:55,003
We could just float.

