00:49:39,384 --> 00:49:44,981
#As the earth turns and the summer's all gone#

651
00:49:45,056 --> 00:49:50,688
#Still without you the show goes on#

652
00:49:56,401 --> 00:49:59,427
You're not breaking any records, Brian.

653
00:49:59,504 --> 00:50:03,099
Goddamn it! Get it on your shoulder!

654
00:50:04,743 --> 00:50:07,439
All right, Stephen. Come on, Stephen!

655
00:50:09,414 --> 00:50:12,076
Come on, Brian. Kick that old man's ass!

656
00:50:16,721 --> 00:50:18,916
Run, damn you!

657
00:50:21,826 --> 00:50:24,693
I'm comin'. I'm comin'!

658
00:50:54,425 --> 00:50:56,825
Aw, shit!

659
00:50:56,895 --> 00:50:58,760
Are you okay?

660
00:50:58,830 --> 00:51:00,821
Yeah.

661
00:51:06,805 --> 00:51:08,739
Run, damn you!

662
00:51:11,376 --> 00:51:15,312
Oh, shit. Okay, roll the hose.

663
00:51:15,380 --> 00:51:17,848
Are you kidding me?

664
00:51:17,916 --> 00:51:20,851
- Roll that hose by myself?
- You heard me.

665
00:51:20,919 --> 00:51:25,720
- What about Tim?
- Aw, shit. What about Tim?

666
00:51:25,790 --> 00:51:28,156
For Christ's sake. Next time I'll let you win.

667
00:51:30,562 --> 00:51:33,861
You got a problem with drilling, Probie?

668
00:51:33,932 --> 00:51:37,925
- Is that it?
- No! I don't have a problem,

669
00:51:38,002 --> 00:51:41,529
but let's just have one drill, Lieutenant,

670
00:51:41,606 --> 00:51:46,168
- not one for the company and one for me.
- Roll the hose now!

671
00:51:46,244 --> 00:51:49,372
I'm not gonna quit, Stephen. You hear me?

672
00:51:49,447 --> 00:51:52,561
I'm not gonna quit.

673
00:51:57,266 --> 00:52:00,030
My baby! My baby is still up there!

674
00:52:00,102 --> 00:52:02,570
- Please, somebody!
- Where's your baby at?

675
00:52:02,638 --> 00:52:05,300
How many men you got in there?

676
00:52:05,374 --> 00:52:07,808
My baby is still up there. Please help me!

677
00:52:07,876 --> 00:52:10,436
Hold on, Steve. Don't go up there.

678
00:52:10,512 --> 00:52:13,777
- Wait for the hose line.
- Brian!

679
00:52:22,558 --> 00:52:25,391
Hey, don't take that kind of shit from it!

680
00:52:25,460 --> 00:52:28,691
Don't let it know you're scared!

681
00:52:30,933 --> 00:52:35,233
- Stephen, we gotta wait for a hose team.
- No time.

682
00:52:42,411 --> 00:52:45,107
Come on!

683
00:52:54,790 --> 00:52:58,920
[Creaking]

684
00:52:58,994 --> 00:53:01,963
- You ready?
- We gotta wait for a hose team.

685
00:53:02,030 --> 00:53:04,897
Jump when I say. It won't get us.

686
00:53:04,967 --> 00:53:07,663
Now! Hold your breath!

687
00:53:09,304 --> 00:53:11,738
[Crying]

688
00:53:25,821 --> 00:53:30,485
Stephen!

689
00:54:24,146 --> 00:54:26,512
- Steve, Steve.
- All right.

690
00:54:26,581 --> 00:54:29,175
- You kicked ass, Bull.
- Way to go, Bull.

691
00:54:29,251 --> 00:54:31,276
Thanks.

692
00:54:34,189 --> 00:54:37,488
Man, that was pretty crazy, huh?

693
00:54:39,227 --> 00:54:42,628
I waited. I would've waited.

694
00:54:42,698 --> 00:54:48,466
- Come on. Don't worry about it.
- You did it, man.

695
00:54:48,537 --> 00:54:52,530
You did it all the way. You were really a hero.

696
00:54:55,577 --> 00:54:59,013
Brian... it's not about being a hero.

697
00:55:00,315 --> 00:55:03,045
I went in because there was a kid up there.

698
00:55:03,118 --> 00:55:07,680
I do what I do because that's my way. And it was Dad's way.

699
00:55:07,756 --> 00:55:11,317
- Maybe it's not everybody's way.
- Dad's way?

700
00:55:11,393 --> 00:55:14,419
He tell you that in a fucking seance, huh?

701
00:55:14,496 --> 00:55:17,056
You said you needed to know something.

702
00:55:17,132 --> 00:55:20,260
What did you learn today, huh?

703
00:55:20,335 --> 00:55:23,998
What if there had been another kid up there?

704
00:55:26,842 --> 00:55:28,969
Oh, I don't know.

705
00:55:30,545 --> 00:55:32,604
What do you think, Brian?

706
00:55:32,681 --> 00:55:35,343
Time to move on?

707
00:55:44,693 --> 00:55:46,752
You're right.

708
00:55:47,996 --> 00:55:51,488
You win, Stephen. You're the best.

709
00:55:56,905 --> 00:55:59,032
Hey, Brian?

710
00:56:08,884 --> 00:56:10,374
Brian.

711
00:56:10,452 --> 00:56:12,886
Hi.

712
00:56:12,954 --> 00:56:16,651
Listen, Jen, I--

713
00:56:16,725 --> 00:56:20,183
I've been thinking about what you said.

714
00:56:20,262 --> 00:56:23,322
If the offer's still on the table, I'd like to talk about it.

715
00:56:26,902 --> 00:56:28,893
Well, great!

716
00:56:28,970 --> 00:56:31,768
That's great, really great news.

717
00:56:31,840 --> 00:56:35,776
The alderman'll be thrilled that you're working with us.

718
00:56:37,612 --> 00:56:39,910
Marty's a good man, Brian.

719
00:56:39,981 --> 00:56:42,973
Yeah.

720
00:57:09,465 --> 00:57:12,229
[Rimgale] So stop me if I got this wrong.

721
00:57:12,301 --> 00:57:15,464
The fire's almost out, you're upstairs on the unburned floor...

722
00:57:15,538 --> 00:57:17,802
- checkin' for heat. Correct?
- Yes, sir.

723
00:57:17,873 --> 00:57:20,239
- Messages for you.
- Thank you.

724
00:57:20,309 --> 00:57:22,300
You've been told by your battalion chief, your captain...

725
00:57:22,378 --> 00:57:25,040
and by me not to do nothin', right?

726
00:57:25,114 --> 00:57:27,309
- Do nothin' until ordered, correct?
- Yes, sir.

727
00:57:27,383 --> 00:57:30,511
Now the itch starts. The glory boy flash starts.

728
00:57:30,586 --> 00:57:32,520
"I'm a hero. Heroes don't stand around."

729
00:57:32,588 --> 00:57:34,749
- You can tell me. That's what it was?
- Yes, sir.

730
00:57:34,824 --> 00:57:37,952
So you punched out a window for ventilation.

731
00:57:38,027 --> 00:57:41,326
Was that before or after you noticed you were standing in a lake of gasoline?

732
00:57:41,397 --> 00:57:43,957
Was that before or after you noticed...

733
00:57:44,033 --> 00:57:47,059
you were standing in a lake of gasoline, you idiot?

734
00:57:47,136 --> 00:57:50,435
Before, sir.

735
00:57:50,506 --> 00:57:53,703
You could have burned, killed, or crispered half that company.

736
00:57:53,776 --> 00:57:58,236
You wrecked the physical evidence that I use to prove that it's arson.

737
00:57:58,314 --> 00:58:02,307
You know how goddamn hard it is to determine the cause.

738
00:58:02,385 --> 00:58:05,513
Now go home and you think about that.

739
00:58:07,890 --> 00:58:10,791
- I'll have to call him back.
- Excuse me.

740
00:58:10,860 --> 00:58:12,851
- Yeah?
- Brian McCaffrey, your new assistant.

741
00:58:12,928 --> 00:58:16,193
Oh, Dennis' kid. Why don't you go find a corner to hide in?

742
00:58:16,265 --> 00:58:18,597
I'll get to you later. I don't wanna deal with you now.

743
00:58:24,807 --> 00:58:26,138
Great.

744
00:58:48,731 --> 00:58:50,722
You still standing there?

745
00:58:53,069 --> 00:58:56,197
I think we should get something straight here now.

746
00:58:56,272 --> 00:58:58,206
I was assigned to this office by the city.

747
00:58:58,274 --> 00:59:00,538
- You better get used to me.
- I know who you were assigned by.

748
00:59:00,609 --> 00:59:03,373
I knew your father too. He was a hell of a fireman.

749
00:59:03,446 --> 00:59:05,380
He had a hell of a reputation.

750
00:59:05,448 --> 00:59:07,882
But it don't cut slack here as far as I'm concerned.

751
00:59:07,950 --> 00:59:11,283
Swayzak sends you here, fine. I gotta eat you. Those are rules.

752
00:59:11,354 --> 00:59:13,322
I got nothin' to say about that.

753
00:59:13,389 --> 00:59:16,449
Swayzak or no, you work for me now.

754
00:59:16,525 --> 00:59:19,050
Step outta line, make one false move, you're outta here.

755
00:59:19,128 --> 00:59:22,894
Don't think you're the first.

756
00:59:22,965 --> 00:59:25,160
- Let's go.
- Where we goin'?

757
00:59:25,234 --> 00:59:26,394
Pest control.

758
00:59:33,242 --> 00:59:36,939
#Shadow, shadow#

759
00:59:37,012 --> 00:59:38,502
Hi, Shadow.

760
00:59:38,581 --> 00:59:41,015
Hi, Ronald. How ya doin'? Stayin' comfortable?

761
00:59:41,083 --> 00:59:45,611
- I didn't think you would make it.
- I wouldn't miss this.

762
00:59:45,688 --> 00:59:47,952
- Who's that?
- He works for me.

763
00:59:48,023 --> 00:59:50,218
Is he a fireman? I like firemen.

764
00:59:50,292 --> 00:59:52,226
You like everybody, Ronald.

765
00:59:52,294 --> 00:59:56,754
Brian McCaffrey. Yeah, sure. No, that's Stephen.

766
00:59:59,101 --> 01:00:01,535
He's the little one with the hat.

767
01:00:01,604 --> 01:00:04,368
Oh, what a treat!

768
01:00:04,440 --> 01:00:08,001
- Hey, do I know you?
- Your dad did.

769
01:00:09,678 --> 01:00:11,771
- Who the hell is this guy?
- Nah, put it away.

770
01:00:11,847 --> 01:00:15,146
Come on, Shadow. He lost his dad to the animal and...

771
01:00:15,217 --> 01:00:18,914
you didn't even tell him who he was coming to see? Tell him.

772
01:00:18,988 --> 01:00:23,118
Let me tell you about Ronald. Ronald likes telephones.

773
01:00:23,192 --> 01:00:25,660
Likes to tape wooden matches to the bell strikers...

774
01:00:25,728 --> 01:00:28,663
and then wrap it in cotton with gasoline.

775
01:00:28,731 --> 01:00:31,723
Had a whole little thing goin', huh? And when you got bored?

776
01:00:31,801 --> 01:00:33,735
What'd you do?

777
01:00:33,803 --> 01:00:38,365
- He started makin' calls.
- Never proved.

778
01:00:38,441 --> 01:00:40,705
Tell him about us down on State Street.

779
01:00:40,776 --> 01:00:44,872
Nah. Nobody cares about that one.

780
01:00:44,947 --> 01:00:48,781
It was your basic warehouse torch I was doin' for the owner.

781
01:00:48,851 --> 01:00:51,684
I mean, they were a cakewalk. I just--

782
01:00:51,754 --> 01:00:56,623
I just lost my concentration and my animal turned on me.

783
01:00:56,692 --> 01:00:58,819
Got the whole place going like hell.

784
01:00:58,894 --> 01:01:02,193
My hair was on fire, my hands,

785
01:01:02,264 --> 01:01:04,528
everything. I was dead.

786
01:01:04,600 --> 01:01:06,625
Then suddenly I was alive. I was pulled out of there...

787
01:01:06,702 --> 01:01:10,229
by my hero, my Shadow here.

788
01:01:10,306 --> 01:01:13,434
Except, he didn't see this big tub of phosphorous, did you?

789
01:01:13,509 --> 01:01:17,878
Explosion lit him up so bright, left his shadow on the wall.

790
01:01:17,947 --> 01:01:21,314
Still shy about rolling up your sleeves, Shadow?

791
01:01:21,383 --> 01:01:23,374
Show him your stomach.

792
01:01:23,452 --> 01:01:27,980
The funny thing about firemen,

793
01:01:28,057 --> 01:01:30,355
night and day, they're always firemen.

794
01:01:30,426 --> 01:01:33,953
[Guard] Ronald Bartel.

795
01:01:34,029 --> 01:01:37,487
All right, the parole board has received...

796
01:01:37,566 --> 01:01:39,864
Mr. Bartel's fitness report,

797
01:01:39,935 --> 01:01:44,736
his I.D. 44, endorsement from his section warden.

798
01:01:44,807 --> 01:01:46,775
Dr. Norris?

799
01:01:46,842 --> 01:01:49,140
As supervising psychiatrist, I would describe...

800
01:01:49,211 --> 01:01:51,771
Mr. Bartel's progress as remarkable.

801
01:01:51,847 --> 01:01:53,838
Taking into account his disability and the six years...

802
01:01:53,916 --> 01:01:57,113
he's already served, I recommend a parole.

803
01:01:57,186 --> 01:01:59,552
Mr. Bartel,

804
01:01:59,622 --> 01:02:02,090
do you regret your crimes?

805
01:02:02,157 --> 01:02:06,321
Yes, and--

806
01:02:06,395 --> 01:02:11,332
and I'm aware of the pain that I have caused.

807
01:02:11,400 --> 01:02:13,868
If released, will you commit these crimes again?

808
01:02:13,936 --> 01:02:15,904
No. No, I won't.

809
01:02:15,971 --> 01:02:19,236
Do you consider yourself ready for society?

810
01:02:19,308 --> 01:02:21,276
Yes, I do.

811
01:02:21,343 --> 01:02:25,507
Yeah, right, Ronald. You're ready, all right.

812
01:02:25,581 --> 01:02:28,175
- Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

813
01:02:28,250 --> 01:02:31,378
- Shadow.
- Remember this?

814
01:02:31,453 --> 01:02:33,614
Remember this, Ronald?

815
01:02:33,689 --> 01:02:35,748
- Remember who it belonged to?
- Mm-hmm.

816
01:02:35,824 --> 01:02:38,258
What did you do to that little girl?

817
01:02:38,327 --> 01:02:41,125
It's not fair, Shadow.

818
01:02:41,196 --> 01:02:43,562
What did you do to that little girl?

819
01:02:52,641 --> 01:02:57,044
I burned her.

820
01:02:57,112 --> 01:02:59,103
You burned her.

821
01:02:59,181 --> 01:03:03,709
What do you do to old ladies, Ronald?

822
01:03:03,786 --> 01:03:05,879
Burn them.

823
01:03:05,955 --> 01:03:08,583
And what about the world, Ronald?

824
01:03:08,657 --> 01:03:11,285
What would you like to do with the whole world?

825
01:03:11,360 --> 01:03:16,195
Burn it all. [Laughing]

826
01:03:22,438 --> 01:03:25,930
See ya next year, Ronald.

827
01:03:55,971 --> 01:03:57,905
[Screams]

828
01:04:04,446 --> 01:04:07,882
[Lieutenant] We figured the body's the owner, some guy named Cosgrove.

829
01:04:07,950 --> 01:04:11,010
Weird blast, though, like that other guy...

830
01:04:11,086 --> 01:04:13,213
who went through the windshield of his own car.

831
01:04:13,288 --> 01:04:16,485
Explosion blew out the flame before the engine got here.

832
01:04:16,558 --> 01:04:20,289
Good for us; not too good for him.

833
01:04:31,674 --> 01:04:33,972
Bring the toolbox.

834
01:04:39,815 --> 01:04:42,045
Tim, get the hot spots.

835
01:04:42,117 --> 01:04:45,883
You in the cheap seats, watch it.

836
01:04:46,855 --> 01:04:48,345
There's Brian.

837
01:04:48,424 --> 01:04:51,951
Well, let's go.

838
01:04:52,027 --> 01:04:55,428
[Rimgale] Hey, McCaffrey, need a special invitation? Come on.

839
01:04:57,132 --> 01:04:59,600
Charge the line, Axe.

840
01:05:01,470 --> 01:05:05,634
- What do you want me to do with this?
- Shhh.

841
01:05:05,708 --> 01:05:08,506
We got heavy smoke stains observed in entry room.

842
01:05:08,577 --> 01:05:10,977
[Rimgale] Smoke demarcation line is very low.

843
01:05:11,046 --> 01:05:14,482
Fire never got hot enough here to cook the soot off.

844
01:05:16,985 --> 01:05:20,443
Come on, you sneaky little son-of-a-bitch.

845
01:05:20,522 --> 01:05:24,014
Come on. Tell me where you came from.

846
01:05:24,093 --> 01:05:26,561
Point me where you started.

847
01:05:26,628 --> 01:05:28,755
Come on.

848
01:05:33,102 --> 01:05:35,627
Burn indicators distended toward northern wall.

849
01:05:35,704 --> 01:05:39,697
Less soot here, more heat.

850
01:05:39,775 --> 01:05:41,970
Lack of discoloration in shattered glass...

851
01:05:42,044 --> 01:05:44,569
indicates slow burn before explosion.

852
01:05:47,549 --> 01:05:50,074
There's some little dead rat critters here.

853
01:05:51,720 --> 01:05:56,248
Fire originated in this room. Took its time.

854
01:05:56,325 --> 01:05:58,259
Hung out.

855
01:05:58,327 --> 01:06:02,559
The air ran out. It couldn't breathe. It was snuffed.

856
01:06:02,631 --> 01:06:05,259
But it wasn't dead.

857
01:06:05,367 --> 01:06:07,961
Must have been all that trapped heat lying low,

858
01:06:08,036 --> 01:06:11,267
waiting for some sucker to give it one big gulp of air.

859
01:06:11,340 --> 01:06:14,332
Another backdraft.

860
01:06:18,580 --> 01:06:22,812
This is our point of origin. Let me have a crowbar.

861
01:06:29,691 --> 01:06:32,785
No sign of accelerants.

862
01:06:35,731 --> 01:06:40,201
Well, if it's arson, somebody figured a new way to hide it.

863
01:06:42,403 --> 01:06:46,134
[Ricco] Okay, we got Alan Seagrave...

864
01:06:46,207 --> 01:06:49,802
and Donald Cosgrove.

865
01:06:49,877 --> 01:06:51,811
Both deaths due to close encounters...

866
01:06:51,879 --> 01:06:55,371
with stationary objects.

867
01:06:55,450 --> 01:06:58,419
We have an office door for Cosgrove...

868
01:06:58,486 --> 01:07:00,716
and, oh, an '87 Porsche for Seagrave.

869
01:07:00,788 --> 01:07:04,656
No nonrelevant traumas.

870
01:07:04,725 --> 01:07:08,593
No significant blood toxicology.

871
01:07:08,663 --> 01:07:12,827
Attitude of both trajectories are consistent with explosion.

872
01:07:12,934 --> 01:07:16,131
They ran the residue you scraped from both front doors.

873
01:07:16,204 --> 01:07:19,139
It's a combination of plumber's putty and rayophene gum.

874
01:07:19,207 --> 01:07:21,175
It burns almost completely away when you light it.

875
01:07:21,242 --> 01:07:23,233
- So it was on both doors?
- Yeah.

876
01:07:23,311 --> 01:07:26,803
Something else I want to show you. You're gonna have to help me.

877
01:07:26,881 --> 01:07:30,282
McCaffrey, why don't you come over and help us?

878
01:07:30,351 --> 01:07:32,876
No, I don't think so. Not in my contract.

879
01:07:32,954 --> 01:07:35,252
I just rewrote your contract.

880
01:07:35,323 --> 01:07:37,723
Come on over and help us.

881
01:07:37,792 --> 01:07:41,523
Anyway, here, we're gonna have to lift him.

882
01:07:41,596 --> 01:07:44,531
Great.

883
01:07:44,599 --> 01:07:48,194
Christ, he's not gonna sell you insurance. Just lift him up.

884
01:07:50,538 --> 01:07:52,836
Hold on.

885
01:07:52,907 --> 01:07:55,171
You see that patch of shirt right there?

886
01:07:55,243 --> 01:07:57,211
We wondered about the discoloration.

887
01:07:57,278 --> 01:07:59,769
So I scraped a piece off and ran a spectro on it.

888
01:07:59,847 --> 01:08:03,874
On a lucky shot, we picked up traces of something.

889
01:08:03,951 --> 01:08:05,919
What was it?

890
01:08:05,987 --> 01:08:08,547
Ah, trychtichlorate.

891
01:08:08,623 --> 01:08:10,955
[Ricco] Nobody around here ever heard of it.

892
01:08:11,025 --> 01:08:13,585
[Rimgale] Yeah, trychtichlorate. It eats magnesium.

893
01:08:13,661 --> 01:08:16,027
It's an absorption catalyst used in toxic waste accidents.

894
01:08:16,097 --> 01:08:18,793
It's rare. They stopped making it a couple of years ago.

895
01:08:18,866 --> 01:08:22,324
We figured it got in his clothes in a gas state from the fire.

896
01:08:22,403 --> 01:08:24,337
What was it doing in the fire?

897
01:08:24,405 --> 01:08:27,033
That's your job. Okay!

898
01:08:27,108 --> 01:08:30,600
[Gurgling]

899
01:08:32,179 --> 01:08:35,808
[Helen] Stephen, what-- What are you doing here?

900
01:08:35,883 --> 01:08:38,408
Just fixin' my roof.

901
01:08:38,486 --> 01:08:42,320
You've gotta stop just showing up on the roof like this.

902
01:08:42,390 --> 01:08:45,188
Look, I just-- I wanted to, I don't know, not exactly...

903
01:08:45,259 --> 01:08:47,318
apologize for the other night, especially since...

904
01:08:47,395 --> 01:08:49,329
- I don't remember much.
- You remember.

905
01:08:49,397 --> 01:08:52,525
Yeah, I know. I just wanted to say, I don't know, something.

906
01:08:52,600 --> 01:08:55,967
The great communicator.

907
01:09:00,575 --> 01:09:04,602
So what's going on, Stephen?

908
01:09:07,415 --> 01:09:12,318
You only bang on the roof when you got something on your mind.

909
01:09:12,386 --> 01:09:14,752
How's Brian doing?

910
01:09:14,822 --> 01:09:19,759
- He's out. He quit.
- He just up and quit for no reason?

911
01:09:19,827 --> 01:09:22,557
I don't care what you heard, Helen, I treated him better...

912
01:09:22,630 --> 01:09:25,098
than any other probie I ever had. All right?

913
01:09:25,166 --> 01:09:27,259
He probably hates my guts...

914
01:09:27,335 --> 01:09:29,860
but at least he finally took a look in the mirror.

915
01:09:29,937 --> 01:09:32,906
So once again, Stephen's right and somebody else is wrong.

916
01:09:32,974 --> 01:09:34,908
You always gotta be right.

917
01:09:34,976 --> 01:09:37,342
- That's such bullshit.
- Yeah? Why?

918
01:09:37,411 --> 01:09:40,574
Because I'm the first to admit it when I'm wrong.

919
01:09:40,648 --> 01:09:42,582
Yeah? How often does that happen?

920
01:09:42,650 --> 01:09:44,709
In a fire? Never!

921
01:09:47,488 --> 01:09:50,048
He would have bought it, Helen.

922
01:09:50,124 --> 01:09:53,651
I'm telling ya, maybe not today, maybe not next year;

923
01:09:53,728 --> 01:09:57,186
but it would have happened. All right? He's my brother.

924
01:09:57,264 --> 01:09:59,232
I couldn't just--

925
01:09:59,300 --> 01:10:01,894
You just couldn't live with that.

926
01:10:07,208 --> 01:10:09,142
McCaffrey.

927
01:10:12,446 --> 01:10:14,414
Yeah?

928
01:10:16,250 --> 01:10:18,445
Take the top off.

929
01:10:22,390 --> 01:10:23,823
Holy shit!

930
01:10:23,891 --> 01:10:26,883
That's it. That's it.

931
01:10:26,961 --> 01:10:30,453
Son-of-a-bitch! This guy is different. He don't love fire.

932
01:10:30,531 --> 01:10:31,793
- Who?
- The killer.

933
01:10:31,866 --> 01:10:34,664
He used magnesium to make it look like an accident.

934
01:10:34,735 --> 01:10:36,498
I got it after we went to see Ronald.

935
01:10:36,570 --> 01:10:38,936
Torchers want to fry the whole goddamn world.

936
01:10:39,006 --> 01:10:42,442
But the fires that killed those guys never burned up that much.

937
01:10:42,510 --> 01:10:46,207
The trychtichlorate hid the magnesium in the plug, but it burned slow.

938
01:10:46,280 --> 01:10:48,373
And he made his burns backdrafts.

939
01:10:48,449 --> 01:10:52,044
- But he killed these guys.
- Could have killed everybody.

940
01:10:52,119 --> 01:10:55,316
Backdraft blew out the flame. That's it. That's the reason.

941
01:10:55,389 --> 01:10:59,519
- What reason?
- Why backdrafts.

942
01:10:59,593 --> 01:11:01,584
Whoever fried Seagrave and Cosgrove...

943
01:11:01,662 --> 01:11:04,426
went to a hell of a lot of trouble to make sure they died by fire.

944
01:11:04,498 --> 01:11:06,762
They also made sure that the fire blew itself out.

945
01:11:06,834 --> 01:11:09,428
So that's why they used the putty in the doors.

946
01:11:10,671 --> 01:11:12,605
What do we got? A torch with a conscience?

947
01:11:12,673 --> 01:11:16,666
No. We got a stone killer trying to make a point.

948
01:11:16,744 --> 01:11:18,939
You can make the call now. It's arson, right?

949
01:11:19,013 --> 01:11:22,141
I'm not calling anyone yet.

950
01:11:22,216 --> 01:11:24,684
You can't rush this. I've seen it too many times before.

951
01:11:24,752 --> 01:11:27,414
I wanna make sure this torch doesn't walk.

952
01:11:27,488 --> 01:11:30,685
We're gonna wait.

953
01:11:30,758 --> 01:11:33,124
[Boat Horn]

954
01:11:35,429 --> 01:11:38,398
Well, well, Mr. McCaffrey.

955
01:11:38,466 --> 01:11:41,367
- Welcome aboard.
- Nice boat you got here.

956
01:11:41,435 --> 01:11:43,494
What? You mean mine?

957
01:11:43,571 --> 01:11:47,632
Well, not yet. Glad to have you as part of the team, Brian.

958
01:11:47,708 --> 01:11:50,404
Let's get a picture with Mr. McCaffrey and myself.

959
01:11:53,180 --> 01:11:55,876
You look good. Yeah, there you go.

960
01:11:55,950 --> 01:11:59,647
Thanks. Hi.

961
01:11:59,720 --> 01:12:01,950
Yeah, have fun now. Great night, isn't it?

962
01:12:02,022 --> 01:12:04,582
[Swayzak] Who is that?

963
01:12:04,658 --> 01:12:07,252
- Larry Dewaay.
- Come on. Larry, how are ya?

964
01:12:07,328 --> 01:12:11,890
[Siren]

965
01:12:29,450 --> 01:12:31,384
Hey.

966
01:12:31,452 --> 01:12:34,285
- Yeah.
- How's the job going?

967
01:12:34,355 --> 01:12:37,654
Okay.

968
01:12:37,725 --> 01:12:41,456
Yeah? ls Rimgale getting any better?

969
01:12:41,529 --> 01:12:44,862
Rimgale's Rimgale. He's just doing his job.

970
01:12:44,932 --> 01:12:47,526
Doing his job? He hasn't done anything.

971
01:12:47,601 --> 01:12:50,035
At this rate, he won't declare it's arson before he retires.

972
01:12:50,104 --> 01:12:54,006
[Laughing And Screaming]

973
01:12:54,074 --> 01:12:57,737
Will you get me out of here?

974
01:12:57,812 --> 01:13:00,713
Otherwise I'm gonna have to go and pick her up.

975
01:13:05,486 --> 01:13:09,286
This is it, one of the oldest fire stations in the city.

976
01:13:09,356 --> 01:13:11,483
What do you think?

977
01:13:11,559 --> 01:13:13,493
- It's homey.
- Shhh!

978
01:13:13,561 --> 01:13:16,724
The guys are sleeping upstairs. You're gonna get me in trouble.

979
01:13:16,797 --> 01:13:20,358
This is my office. Impressive, huh?

980
01:13:20,434 --> 01:13:23,665
Yes, it's very nice.

981
01:13:23,737 --> 01:13:26,729
Lot of tradition locked up in this old house.

982
01:13:26,807 --> 01:13:28,775
See those doors?

983
01:13:28,843 --> 01:13:32,609
They lead to the hay loft when they used to have the old horse-drawn engines.

984
01:13:32,680 --> 01:13:36,138
Lot different then.

985
01:13:36,217 --> 01:13:38,685
But kind of the same, you know?

986
01:13:44,325 --> 01:13:46,691
Do you miss it?

987
01:13:48,596 --> 01:13:50,621
You seem like you do.

988
01:13:50,698 --> 01:13:54,691
Well,

989
01:13:54,768 --> 01:13:56,702
when I came back,

990
01:13:56,770 --> 01:14:00,729
I, uh-- I knew.

991
01:14:00,808 --> 01:14:03,464
I knew that I really wanted to be a fireman.

992
01:14:03,597 --> 01:14:06,430
Then why'd you quit?

993
01:14:08,002 --> 01:14:12,666
I should have said I wanted to be a good one.

994
01:14:21,315 --> 01:14:24,216
So show me your fire truck.

995
01:14:27,955 --> 01:14:29,923
Shhh!

996
01:14:43,170 --> 01:14:46,697
[Siren]

997
01:14:50,878 --> 01:14:54,871
[Pengelly] Mask up, lads. Bring that sledge.

998
01:14:54,949 --> 01:14:59,386
[Alarm Ringing]

999
01:15:00,921 --> 01:15:02,411
Where is it?

1000
01:15:02,490 --> 01:15:05,254
I don't know. There's alarms goin' off on three floors.

1001
01:15:14,268 --> 01:15:17,032
This alarm system's been screwing up since they built--

1002
01:15:17,104 --> 01:15:20,540
- 10? 29?
- Yeah.

1003
01:15:32,453 --> 01:15:36,389
How do we know if the floor's gonna be on fire?

1004
01:15:36,457 --> 01:15:38,482
Well, when the doors open,

1005
01:15:38,559 --> 01:15:40,584
if it's hot,

1006
01:15:40,661 --> 01:15:43,391
- don't get out.
- [Snickering]

1007
01:15:48,869 --> 01:15:51,429
We're gonna start on this side. I'll meet you down at the end.

1008
01:15:57,077 --> 01:16:01,241
- All right, come on. Come on.
- High-rise gigs give me the creeps.

1009
01:16:03,083 --> 01:16:05,745
Bull, we're early on this one again...

1010
01:16:05,820 --> 01:16:08,687
and it ain't even broke out yet. We're one short with Brian gone.

1011
01:16:08,756 --> 01:16:11,691
- Wait for the next-in engines.
- Let's catch it before it breaks out.

1012
01:16:14,128 --> 01:16:17,495
- You want to learn something?
- Yeah, I do.

1013
01:16:17,565 --> 01:16:19,965
Axe, go with Pengelly. Take the other side.

1014
01:16:20,034 --> 01:16:23,868
- Don't split us up again. It ain't safe.
- I haven't got time for this.

1015
01:16:23,938 --> 01:16:28,773
- Then let me take the lead.
- Do your job; they need a line.

1016
01:16:30,878 --> 01:16:32,846
Come on. Come on, Axe.

1017
01:16:44,592 --> 01:16:48,323
Oh, you're so very sly; but, so am I.

1018
01:17:09,650 --> 01:17:12,380
She's hot and smoky...

1019
01:17:12,453 --> 01:17:14,512
but she's not rollin' yet.

1020
01:17:28,002 --> 01:17:29,936
- [Fire Bell]
- Shit!

1021
01:17:31,472 --> 01:17:35,374
[Dispatcher] Hello, 51. You follow 17 in the truck.

1022
01:17:35,442 --> 01:17:39,469
[Dispatcher] 11201 South Clark. It's a cancel.

1023
01:17:39,546 --> 01:17:42,140
[Dispatcher] 11021 South Clark.

1024
01:17:42,216 --> 01:17:47,153
- South Clark.
- What time is it, anyway?

1025
01:17:49,223 --> 01:17:53,023
[Siren]

1026
01:17:55,963 --> 01:17:58,022
[Truck Horn And Siren]

1027
01:18:04,104 --> 01:18:06,834
All right, take it.

1028
01:18:12,346 --> 01:18:14,576
Wait, wait. Make sure you check it first.

1029
01:18:14,648 --> 01:18:16,582
Oh, yeah.

1030
01:18:21,255 --> 01:18:23,519
[Siren]

1031
01:18:37,171 --> 01:18:40,629
- Howdy, boys.
- Brian!

1032
01:18:40,708 --> 01:18:43,199
- Here we go. Now get that mask back on.
- Right.

1033
01:18:43,277 --> 01:18:46,212
Clear!

1034
01:18:46,280 --> 01:18:48,214
Stay here.

1035
01:19:06,200 --> 01:19:08,327
Check that door for heat, Tim?

1036
01:19:14,908 --> 01:19:16,842
Tim!

1037
01:19:21,115 --> 01:19:24,312
[Screams]

1038
01:19:30,891 --> 01:19:33,359
Watch out, Steve. I got him. Move off.

1039
01:19:34,661 --> 01:19:38,119
Put it out!

1040
01:19:38,198 --> 01:19:40,393
Stretcher!

1041
01:19:40,467 --> 01:19:42,833
[Pengelly] Get the goddamn stretcher.

1042
01:19:42,903 --> 01:19:47,363
Everybody over here. Through here. Through here.

1043
01:19:47,441 --> 01:19:49,739
Get that stretcher over here.

1044
01:19:49,810 --> 01:19:51,778
What the hell happened?

1045
01:19:54,415 --> 01:19:56,440
Tim! Tim! How'd it happen?

1046
01:19:56,517 --> 01:19:58,781
Breathe, Tim, breathe.

1047
01:20:00,788 --> 01:20:02,517
Get him in there!

1048
01:20:02,589 --> 01:20:04,887
Come on!

1049
01:20:04,958 --> 01:20:08,394
- You're all right.
- Come on! Hang on, kid!

1050
01:20:49,436 --> 01:20:52,132
- Hey, Shadow, I got one here.
- Oh, Christ.

1051
01:20:54,241 --> 01:20:56,175
Some guy named Holcomb.

1052
01:21:01,582 --> 01:21:04,346
Steve.

1053
01:21:04,418 --> 01:21:06,943
[Pengelly] Steve.

1054
01:21:07,020 --> 01:21:09,079
Steve, you all right?

1055
01:21:29,610 --> 01:21:32,909
- How is he?
- He's alive.

1056
01:21:38,852 --> 01:21:42,310
- Is he gonna make it?
- They're not saying.

1057
01:21:43,857 --> 01:21:45,791
He's in there.

1058
01:21:47,961 --> 01:21:49,895
I'm sorry. You can't come in now.

1059
01:21:49,963 --> 01:21:51,954
Please stay outside.

1060
01:21:56,370 --> 01:21:58,338
I should have been there.

1061
01:21:58,405 --> 01:22:00,270
None of us should have been there, Brian.

1062
01:22:03,343 --> 01:22:05,402
Don't tell me about the chance I'm taking.

1063
01:22:05,479 --> 01:22:07,674
- You were costing me time.
- You didn't wait for back-up.

1064
01:22:07,748 --> 01:22:11,479
- You were wrong.
- What the hell is your trouble?

1065
01:22:13,987 --> 01:22:16,046
- This part of your investigation?
- You had to do it.

1066
01:22:16,123 --> 01:22:18,387
You had to be myth man, taking another fire bare-handed...

1067
01:22:18,458 --> 01:22:20,585
- instead of looking out for the probie.
- We need space.

1068
01:22:20,661 --> 01:22:23,459
- Is that what happened?
- I had that fire. He didn't listen.

1069
01:22:23,530 --> 01:22:25,691
He's a candidate, your responsibility.

1070
01:22:25,766 --> 01:22:27,700
You shouldn't have had him up there in the first place.

1071
01:22:27,768 --> 01:22:29,736
You burned him, Stephen.

1072
01:22:29,803 --> 01:22:32,795
- Fuck you.
- Don't you walk away from me.

1073
01:22:46,153 --> 01:22:48,121
Yo, Brian. Let's go.

1074
01:22:48,188 --> 01:22:51,214
Goddamn it! Get him off!

1075
01:22:51,291 --> 01:22:53,657
Come on!

1076
01:22:53,727 --> 01:22:55,354
Easy, man.

1077
01:22:55,429 --> 01:22:57,397
Loosen up! You're just making things worse.

1078
01:22:57,464 --> 01:22:59,489
- Relax. Forget about it.
- Come on. Come on.

1079
01:23:27,020 --> 01:23:30,547
- Inspector.
- Alderman.

1080
01:23:36,263 --> 01:23:38,197
Chinese sponge cake?

1081
01:23:38,265 --> 01:23:40,733
When are you gonna catch the prick that's doing this, Don?

1082
01:23:40,801 --> 01:23:43,895
- Don?
- Don't you have any leads?

1083
01:23:43,970 --> 01:23:46,530
No, Marty, I don't.

1084
01:23:46,606 --> 01:23:49,404
We haven't found any connection between the victims at all.

1085
01:23:49,476 --> 01:23:53,037
Jesus Christ. Open your eyes.

1086
01:23:53,113 --> 01:23:55,172
You got Seagrave, Cosgrove...

1087
01:23:55,248 --> 01:23:57,580
- and now Holcomb.
- Holcomb?

1088
01:23:57,651 --> 01:24:00,848
Put 'em together. It's a goddamn list.

1089
01:24:00,921 --> 01:24:02,855
I didn't know the name of that victim had been released?

1090
01:24:21,007 --> 01:24:22,941
Hey, John.

1091
01:24:23,009 --> 01:24:24,943
[Fireman] Morning.

1092
01:24:27,747 --> 01:24:30,944
I'll do whatever you want me to do.

1093
01:24:33,987 --> 01:24:37,548
I want to help you nail that son-of-a-bitch that burned Tim.

1094
01:24:37,624 --> 01:24:41,185
Show me how.

1095
01:24:50,904 --> 01:24:54,169
Thought old Marty was acting a little strange.

1096
01:24:54,241 --> 01:24:59,008
He's right. There's residue.

1097
01:24:59,079 --> 01:25:01,479
Holcomb is the third victim.

1098
01:25:03,917 --> 01:25:06,715
The backdraft was set up somewhere in there.

1099
01:25:06,786 --> 01:25:09,152
Fried Holcomb when he opened the inner door.

1100
01:25:11,591 --> 01:25:14,025
But the outer door held and it waited for Tim.

1101
01:25:17,864 --> 01:25:20,526
In a word, Brian,

1102
01:25:20,600 --> 01:25:23,125
what is this job all about?

1103
01:25:23,203 --> 01:25:24,864
Fire.

1104
01:25:42,222 --> 01:25:44,417
It's a living thing, Brian.

1105
01:25:44,491 --> 01:25:48,018
It breathes, it eats,

1106
01:25:48,094 --> 01:25:50,085
and it hates.

1107
01:25:50,163 --> 01:25:53,690
The only way to beat it...

1108
01:25:53,767 --> 01:25:56,292
is to think like it;

1109
01:25:56,369 --> 01:25:59,634
to know this flame will spread this way across the door...

1110
01:25:59,706 --> 01:26:01,640
and up across the ceiling;

1111
01:26:01,708 --> 01:26:04,142
not because of the physics of flammable liquids,

1112
01:26:04,210 --> 01:26:07,008
but because it wants to.

1113
01:26:07,080 --> 01:26:11,574
Some guys, fire owns 'em. Makes 'em fight it on its level.

1114
01:26:11,651 --> 01:26:15,246
The only way to truly kill it...

1115
01:26:15,322 --> 01:26:19,520
is to love it a little, just like Ronald.

1116
01:26:35,675 --> 01:26:38,269
- Hi.
- Hi.

1117
01:26:38,345 --> 01:26:42,577
- I heard your friend's gonna be okay.
- Thanks.

1118
01:26:42,649 --> 01:26:44,742
We checked and your boss was partners...

1119
01:26:44,818 --> 01:26:47,844
with all the murder victims in a company called Lakeside Dynamics.

1120
01:26:47,921 --> 01:26:51,516
He's keeping that a secret. I wanna know why.

1121
01:26:55,328 --> 01:26:59,958
- I don't know anything about that.
- You might be able to find out.

1122
01:27:00,033 --> 01:27:03,662
- Get me his files.
- Do you know what you're asking?

1123
01:27:03,737 --> 01:27:05,068
Yeah.

1124
01:27:05,138 --> 01:27:08,471
Four years ago I was punching a cash register.

1125
01:27:08,541 --> 01:27:11,066
Two years ago, Marty Swayzak didn't even know my name.

1126
01:27:11,144 --> 01:27:13,078
I was bringing the guy coffee.

1127
01:27:13,146 --> 01:27:15,671
I practically run that office now.

1128
01:27:15,749 --> 01:27:19,310
And Marty-- He believes in me.

1129
01:27:19,386 --> 01:27:21,911
I just don't--

1130
01:27:23,990 --> 01:27:25,924
You're asking me to throw that all away.

1131
01:27:25,992 --> 01:27:28,483
Your boss is a liar.

1132
01:27:49,816 --> 01:27:53,752
Stephen?

1133
01:27:53,820 --> 01:27:57,654
I'm sorry, Helen. I just couldn't sleep.

1134
01:28:01,061 --> 01:28:03,757
Well, what's wrong?

1135
01:28:03,830 --> 01:28:06,799
It used to be real clear.

1136
01:28:06,866 --> 01:28:08,800
When I was a kid,

1137
01:28:11,171 --> 01:28:14,766
what meant most to me about this job was...

1138
01:28:14,841 --> 01:28:17,241
no "ifs."

1139
01:28:17,310 --> 01:28:20,746
Somebody called the fire department, we came.

1140
01:28:20,814 --> 01:28:23,612
We just showed up.

1141
01:28:27,987 --> 01:28:30,888
Those guys, they just don't know how much I love 'em.

1142
01:28:37,063 --> 01:28:40,032
You don't leave people hangin'.

1143
01:28:43,470 --> 01:28:46,530
It holds everything up, doesn't it?

1144
01:28:46,606 --> 01:28:49,632
Loyalty.

1145
01:28:49,709 --> 01:28:51,700
I don't get it.

1146
01:28:51,778 --> 01:28:55,714
"Till death do us part." Isn't that what you heard, Helen?

1147
01:28:55,782 --> 01:28:59,081
You go, we go. It's all the same...

1148
01:28:59,152 --> 01:29:01,177
piece of shit without that, isn't it?

1149
01:29:01,254 --> 01:29:05,486
It's the end of everything.

1150
01:29:11,231 --> 01:29:14,257
I'm sorry I came.

1151
01:29:16,436 --> 01:29:19,428
There's just nobody I can talk to.

1152
01:29:24,344 --> 01:29:28,303
I really miss you.

1153
01:30:14,327 --> 01:30:19,026
[Stephen] You sure you really want to put grape jelly in the eggs?

1154
01:30:19,098 --> 01:30:22,659
Yeah, it's part of my formula. It's an experiment.

1155
01:30:22,735 --> 01:30:24,703
- It's an experiment?
- Yeah.

1156
01:30:24,771 --> 01:30:26,705
Let's get these eggs going.

1157
01:30:26,773 --> 01:30:28,832
- Hey, I want to do that.
- Can you do it?

1158
01:30:28,908 --> 01:30:32,810
That's good.

1159
01:30:34,881 --> 01:30:37,679
I'll put that in the formula.

1160
01:30:37,750 --> 01:30:39,843
- You gonna leave the shells?
- Yeah.

1161
01:30:39,919 --> 01:30:43,013
- They're part of the formula?
- Yeah.

1162
01:30:43,089 --> 01:30:46,547
I guess you know what you're doing.

1163
01:30:46,626 --> 01:30:50,494
- I know what I'm doing.
- Uh-oh.

1164
01:30:50,563 --> 01:30:52,497
Mom!

1165
01:30:52,565 --> 01:30:55,193
I didn't know you'd be up so early.

1166
01:30:55,268 --> 01:30:58,863
Mom, go back to bed. We're making you breakfast in bed.

1167
01:31:04,777 --> 01:31:07,439
- Stephen, can I talk to you a minute?
- Yeah.

1168
01:31:07,513 --> 01:31:10,073
You keep going there. You're doing good.

1169
01:31:10,149 --> 01:31:12,115
He knows what he's doin'.

1170
01:31:12,248 --> 01:31:16,548
He told me he likes those piano lessons you got him taking.

1171
01:31:16,619 --> 01:31:20,350
It's just I don't want to confuse him, you know.

1172
01:31:20,423 --> 01:31:24,484
I knew who you were when we got married.

1173
01:31:24,561 --> 01:31:26,756
I knew how you did things.

1174
01:31:29,265 --> 01:31:31,199
And--

1175
01:31:32,302 --> 01:31:35,738
I mean, you haven't--

1176
01:31:35,805 --> 01:31:38,000
I just can't anymore.

1177
01:31:38,074 --> 01:31:41,168
I just-- you know,

1178
01:31:41,244 --> 01:31:45,476
I gotta worry about Sean.

1179
01:31:45,548 --> 01:31:48,449
- Yeah.
- I mean, you're the best.

1180
01:31:48,518 --> 01:31:50,884
You really are.

1181
01:31:50,954 --> 01:31:54,947
But the chances that you take just--

1182
01:31:57,560 --> 01:31:59,528
You scare me now.

1183
01:32:08,405 --> 01:32:10,532
Sean.

1184
01:32:10,607 --> 01:32:13,269
Listen, I, uh--

1185
01:32:13,343 --> 01:32:15,311
I blew it.

1186
01:32:15,378 --> 01:32:18,006
I forgot that I gotta work this morning.

1187
01:32:18,081 --> 01:32:21,016
So, um--

1188
01:32:21,084 --> 01:32:24,019
That's all right. We'll just do it again next Saturday.

1189
01:32:24,087 --> 01:32:26,885
- All right?
- Mom's crying.

1190
01:32:40,970 --> 01:32:44,167
The latest polls came in, Marty.

1191
01:32:48,978 --> 01:32:50,912
Marty?

1192
01:33:00,089 --> 01:33:02,023
Jesus Christ, Marty.

1193
01:33:02,091 --> 01:33:05,720
What's going on?

1194
01:33:05,795 --> 01:33:09,128
We have a city planners meeting in 15 minutes.

1195
01:33:09,199 --> 01:33:12,259
Marty.

1196
01:33:18,007 --> 01:33:22,068
You've gotta level with me, Marty.

1197
01:33:22,145 --> 01:33:26,104
Is there something about these deaths you're not telling me?

1198
01:33:26,182 --> 01:33:30,380
No.

1199
01:33:53,843 --> 01:33:57,279
- What's this?
- Just take it.

1200
01:34:15,031 --> 01:34:19,161
Rimgale's gonna wanna talk to Swayzak about this.

1201
01:34:19,235 --> 01:34:23,103
I'm sorry.

1202
01:34:23,172 --> 01:34:26,869
That's a dumb thing to say.

1203
01:34:26,943 --> 01:34:29,468
You're right.

1204
01:34:29,546 --> 01:34:33,778
Good-bye, Brian.

1205
01:34:39,622 --> 01:34:42,216
What the hell you do with this thing?

1206
01:34:42,292 --> 01:34:44,453
What do you mean? I drove it, Joe.

1207
01:34:44,527 --> 01:34:47,462
This is a copy of Swayzak's report that we know is bullshit;

1208
01:34:47,530 --> 01:34:50,624
but we could never argue with the numbers because they're airtight.

1209
01:34:50,700 --> 01:34:53,533
This file she gave you proves it's phoney.

1210
01:34:53,603 --> 01:34:57,061
I checked on the firm that recommended the cuts to Swayzak's task force.

1211
01:34:57,140 --> 01:34:59,506
They've done exactly one job, a manpower study.

1212
01:34:59,576 --> 01:35:02,511
I checked further and it's not even a company. No employees... nothing.

1213
01:35:02,579 --> 01:35:06,174
- Just a P.O. box.
- I wonder who wrote that report.

1214
01:35:06,249 --> 01:35:09,412
- Someone who knows how to work numbers.
- Exactly.

1215
01:35:09,485 --> 01:35:13,148
Like a bunch of dead financial wizards.

1216
01:35:13,222 --> 01:35:17,056
- Seagrave, Holcomb, Cosgrove--
- And Swayzak.

1217
01:35:17,126 --> 01:35:20,254
Why did he go through this trouble to cut firehouses?

1218
01:35:20,330 --> 01:35:23,766
When a firehouse closes, Swayzak converts it into a community center.

1219
01:35:23,833 --> 01:35:26,461
- That's sweet.
- Lakeside Dynamics, remember them?

1220
01:35:26,536 --> 01:35:28,834
They get all the expensive construction work.

1221
01:35:28,905 --> 01:35:31,305
I'm telling you, this is a total scam.

1222
01:35:31,374 --> 01:35:34,537
These guys were making a ton of money.

1223
01:35:34,611 --> 01:35:39,727
It's time we had a little talk with Mr. Swayzak. Let's go.

1224
01:35:58,612 --> 01:36:00,944
Mr. Swayzak?

1225
01:36:05,953 --> 01:36:08,114
Gas. Check in there.

1226
01:36:10,858 --> 01:36:14,055
[Hissing]

1227
01:36:26,640 --> 01:36:28,574
Aaah!

1228
01:36:30,544 --> 01:36:33,741
[Screaming]

1229
01:36:52,600 --> 01:36:54,693
Come on. Come on!

1230
01:37:09,950 --> 01:37:12,817
- Let's go. Come on!
- [Coughing]

1231
01:37:36,310 --> 01:37:40,440
- [Coughing]
- Hey, kid.

1232
01:37:40,514 --> 01:37:42,539
I think I've got a problem here.

1233
01:37:50,825 --> 01:37:54,090
Is it true that you were rescued by the fire department's arson team?

1234
01:37:54,161 --> 01:37:56,629
That's quite a bunch of guys, huh?

1235
01:37:59,166 --> 01:38:02,329
I'm so goddamn helpless here.

1236
01:38:02,403 --> 01:38:04,564
I can't do a fucking thing.

1237
01:38:04,638 --> 01:38:07,903
[Sighs]

1238
01:38:07,975 --> 01:38:12,344
- What do you want me to do?
- I've been lying here thinkin'.

1239
01:38:12,413 --> 01:38:17,350
For hours... thinkin' and thinkin' and thinkin'.

1240
01:38:17,418 --> 01:38:21,115
We're close. We're close.

1241
01:38:21,188 --> 01:38:23,122
But we're not lookin' in the right place,

1242
01:38:23,190 --> 01:38:25,124
not in the right place.

1243
01:38:28,529 --> 01:38:33,557
So, you've come to pick Ronald's brains...

1244
01:38:33,634 --> 01:38:37,866
because nobody knows the animal like Ronald.

1245
01:38:44,778 --> 01:38:47,542
It must've looked like it was going to be...

1246
01:38:47,615 --> 01:38:51,346
a medium deal, didn't it, when your father bought it?

1247
01:38:51,418 --> 01:38:53,750
What?

1248
01:38:53,821 --> 01:38:59,521
Did you watch him when he made that ballsy jump and saved--

1249
01:38:59,593 --> 01:39:01,754
I didn't come to talk about my father.

1250
01:39:01,829 --> 01:39:05,162
I sent away for a copy of that "Life Magazine"...

1251
01:39:05,232 --> 01:39:08,167
with your picture on the cover.

1252
01:39:08,235 --> 01:39:10,601
It's a collectible.

1253
01:39:10,671 --> 01:39:13,765
- Who's doing this, Ronald?
- Wrong question.

1254
01:39:13,841 --> 01:39:16,275
Who isn't?

1255
01:39:16,343 --> 01:39:18,436
It isn't a spark, is it? Because there isn't enough damage...

1256
01:39:18,512 --> 01:39:20,878
and he wouldn't have had any fun.

1257
01:39:20,948 --> 01:39:24,782
It isn't an insurance pro because there isn't any profit.

1258
01:39:24,852 --> 01:39:27,343
- Who does that leave us with?
- What's his tool?

1259
01:39:27,421 --> 01:39:31,380
How does he do it? How does he talk to the fire?

1260
01:39:31,458 --> 01:39:35,019
- The outlets.
- No.

1261
01:39:35,095 --> 01:39:38,360
That's a probie. That's beneath you, Brian.

1262
01:39:40,501 --> 01:39:44,733
Trychtichlorate.

1263
01:39:44,805 --> 01:39:48,332
Very good. Very good.

1264
01:39:48,409 --> 01:39:52,743
You still haven't put it together?

1265
01:39:52,813 --> 01:39:55,043
- I have.
- Then who, Ronald?

1266
01:39:55,115 --> 01:39:59,245
You wanna know who?

1267
01:40:01,355 --> 01:40:04,654
I wanna know...

1268
01:40:04,725 --> 01:40:08,821
if this kid really wanted to be...

1269
01:40:08,896 --> 01:40:11,091
just like his dad.

1270
01:40:15,436 --> 01:40:18,633
Did he?

1271
01:40:23,444 --> 01:40:25,378
Okay.

1272
01:40:25,446 --> 01:40:27,937
I'm outta here.

1273
01:40:28,015 --> 01:40:32,111
All right! I wanted to be him, okay?

1274
01:40:38,359 --> 01:40:40,589
I wanted to be him more than anything.

1275
01:40:40,661 --> 01:40:43,027
You loved him.

1276
01:40:43,097 --> 01:40:46,430
Yeah.

1277
01:40:46,500 --> 01:40:51,096
You watched him dance with the animal. You saw your dad burn.

1278
01:40:51,171 --> 01:40:54,538
Fuck you, Ronald! Who the hell's doin' this?

1279
01:40:54,608 --> 01:40:57,668
Did it look at you?

1280
01:40:59,713 --> 01:41:01,977
[Whispering] Did the fire look at you?

1281
01:41:04,852 --> 01:41:07,878
It did.

1282
01:41:17,831 --> 01:41:19,765
Ohhh.

1283
01:41:25,372 --> 01:41:29,706
Our worlds aren't that far apart, are they?

1284
01:41:29,777 --> 01:41:32,678
So...

1285
01:41:32,746 --> 01:41:38,309
whoever did this, really knows the animal well, don't they?

1286
01:41:38,385 --> 01:41:42,014
They know him real well but they won't let him loose.

1287
01:41:42,089 --> 01:41:44,523
They won't let him have fun so they don't love him.

1288
01:41:44,591 --> 01:41:47,355
Who doesn't love fire...

1289
01:41:47,428 --> 01:41:51,023
and is around trychtichlorate all day long?

1290
01:41:51,098 --> 01:41:53,931
Oh, my God!

1291
01:41:59,106 --> 01:42:02,940
That wasn't such a long walk after all, was it?

1292
01:42:16,357 --> 01:42:19,121
Oh, God.

1293
01:42:19,193 --> 01:42:23,994
Goddamn it, Stephen.

1294
01:42:24,064 --> 01:42:26,794
[Door Shutting]

1295
01:42:32,172 --> 01:42:37,109
Hey, what's goin' on?

1296
01:42:37,177 --> 01:42:41,807
I just came by to see how you were doing?

1297
01:42:42,816 --> 01:42:46,047
How am I doin'?

1298
01:42:46,120 --> 01:42:49,647
Well, I'm sellin' Dad's boat.

1299
01:42:52,493 --> 01:42:56,361
Guy comin' by in a few minutes to take a look at it.

1300
01:42:58,365 --> 01:43:00,299
What are you gonna do?

1301
01:43:00,367 --> 01:43:03,859
I mean, where you going?

1302
01:43:06,940 --> 01:43:09,966
I didn't say I was goin' anywhere.

1303
01:43:12,546 --> 01:43:14,707
Look, I gotta-- I gotta get back.

1304
01:43:14,782 --> 01:43:17,376
- There's somethin' I'm supposed to do.
- What?

1305
01:43:17,451 --> 01:43:20,249
What do you gotta do?

1306
01:43:22,556 --> 01:43:25,024
Look at you.

1307
01:43:25,092 --> 01:43:29,495
Look at your face! All the things you must be thinkin'.

1308
01:43:29,563 --> 01:43:33,260
You really hate my guts, don't you?

1309
01:43:33,333 --> 01:43:36,894
You know something, Brian? That's all right.

1310
01:43:36,970 --> 01:43:39,370
- Maybe we should talk abou--
- You don't like me...

1311
01:43:39,440 --> 01:43:42,637
because I was no genius in the way I raised you. Is that it?

1312
01:43:42,709 --> 01:43:45,837
Dad was gone! What was I supposed to do?

1313
01:43:45,913 --> 01:43:48,780
- You tell me.
- Forget it. It's okay.

1314
01:43:48,849 --> 01:43:52,182
I tried. I wanted so many things for you...

1315
01:43:52,252 --> 01:43:55,187
that I couldn't even hope for.

1316
01:43:55,255 --> 01:43:59,123
Because after that, I had no choices!

1317
01:44:05,265 --> 01:44:08,792
Well, I'm not your father.

1318
01:44:08,869 --> 01:44:10,962
You got somewhere to go, go.

1319
01:44:18,512 --> 01:44:21,447
People change, huh, Brian?

1320
01:44:21,515 --> 01:44:24,348
Sometimes right when you're lookin' at 'em.

1321
01:44:27,154 --> 01:44:30,317
What's going on with you?

1322
01:44:30,390 --> 01:44:33,848
I don't know.

1323
01:44:33,927 --> 01:44:36,259
Do you?

1324
01:44:36,330 --> 01:44:38,798
I gotta go.

1325
01:45:52,952 --> 01:45:59,824
[Remembering: Roaring Fire]

1326
01:45:59,893 --> 01:46:03,385
[Screaming]

1327
01:46:18,144 --> 01:46:20,408
[Fire Bell]

1328
01:46:23,183 --> 01:46:26,710
[Dispatcher] Attention, all units responding.

1329
01:46:26,786 --> 01:46:31,086
This is gonna be a hazardous materials response at a chemical plant.

1330
01:46:32,892 --> 01:46:35,986
[Fire Bell]

1331
01:46:37,997 --> 01:46:41,296
- Stephen? Has Stephen gotten back yet?
- He just pulled up.

1332
01:46:47,006 --> 01:46:50,965
- Is it Adcox?
- How do you know?

1333
01:46:55,782 --> 01:46:59,183
I didn't until you came to the boat lookin' for those chemicals.

1334
01:46:59,252 --> 01:47:01,812
- Lookin' for me.
- What were they doing on the boat?

1335
01:47:01,888 --> 01:47:04,288
Axe gave 'em to me. They're cleaning shit.

1336
01:47:04,357 --> 01:47:06,723
- We gotta roll!
- I'll be there in a minute.

1337
01:47:06,793 --> 01:47:08,727
I gotta go to Rimgale with this.

1338
01:47:08,795 --> 01:47:11,263
- They're pullin' a box.
- I'll be there!

1339
01:47:11,331 --> 01:47:14,767
- Stephen!
- Wait! I'm his lieutenant.

1340
01:47:14,834 --> 01:47:16,825
I'll handle it.

1341
01:47:16,903 --> 01:47:20,134
Stephen?

1342
01:47:20,206 --> 01:47:22,401
Are you a part of this?

1343
01:47:22,475 --> 01:47:25,342
No.

1344
01:47:25,411 --> 01:47:28,312
You're sure?

1345
01:47:28,381 --> 01:47:32,181
That's the only thing I am sure of anymore.

1346
01:47:32,252 --> 01:47:34,652
Bull, we need you.

1347
01:47:45,098 --> 01:47:47,464
Jesus Christ!

1348
01:47:47,534 --> 01:47:49,365
Stephen!

1349
01:47:53,873 --> 01:47:55,898
Stephen!

1350
01:47:55,975 --> 01:47:57,966
Shit!

1351
01:48:05,552 --> 01:48:10,012
[Siren And Horn Blasts]

1352
01:48:42,755 --> 01:48:44,689
[Horn Blast]

1353
01:48:56,703 --> 01:48:58,898
[Pengelly] Get out of the way!

1354
01:49:12,852 --> 01:49:14,786
[Moaning]

1355
01:49:14,854 --> 01:49:17,516
- You all right?
- You all right, Peng?

1356
01:49:17,590 --> 01:49:19,615
- Everybody all right?
- You okay?

1357
01:49:19,692 --> 01:49:21,683
Yeah. Help me out.

1358
01:49:37,777 --> 01:49:40,177
Where's 17?

1359
01:49:40,246 --> 01:49:42,339
- I don't know.
- Shit!

1360
01:49:45,318 --> 01:49:47,479
Stephen!

1361
01:49:50,290 --> 01:49:53,225
- Where's 17?
- 17's on the roof.

1362
01:49:53,293 --> 01:49:56,387
[Captain] Mask up. We got a chemical fire.

1363
01:50:28,728 --> 01:50:30,696
[Indistinct]

1364
01:50:38,671 --> 01:50:41,663
[Chief] We're pullin' the plug.

1365
01:50:41,741 --> 01:50:44,904
Everybody off the roof, now!

1366
01:50:44,977 --> 01:50:48,071
[Stephen] Jesus Christ, Axe. You don't understand.

1367
01:50:48,147 --> 01:50:51,480
[Adcox] My cousin, Sally, used to work at Swayzak's office.

1368
01:50:51,551 --> 01:50:53,576
She saw the files. She saw what he did.

1369
01:50:53,653 --> 01:50:56,520
- You set me up with those chemicals?
- I'm tryin' to explain.

1370
01:50:56,589 --> 01:50:59,080
- Stephen.
- You back off!

1371
01:50:59,158 --> 01:51:01,353
- Axe.
- Somebody had to stop these pricks.

1372
01:51:01,427 --> 01:51:04,658
- Are you thinkin'? You burned people!
- You didn't see.

1373
01:51:04,731 --> 01:51:08,997
- You're a fireman.
- When Sally showed me Swayzak's files--

1374
01:51:09,068 --> 01:51:12,060
- I should've let you in on it.
- In on murder?

1375
01:51:12,138 --> 01:51:16,632
Those assholes were closin' firehouses, gettin' our friends killed for money.

1376
01:51:16,709 --> 01:51:20,270
- I had to do it for the department!
- For Tim?

1377
01:51:20,346 --> 01:51:22,871
- That was an accident.
- Did you start that fire?

1378
01:51:22,949 --> 01:51:26,146
Why'd you have to go in there so fucking early?

1379
01:51:26,219 --> 01:51:28,153
That's why you wanted me to wait.

1380
01:51:28,221 --> 01:51:30,712
- Let me finish Swayzak!
- No. It's over.

1381
01:51:30,790 --> 01:51:34,317
Your dad would puke if he saw how you shit on his department.

1382
01:51:34,394 --> 01:51:38,091
- What would he say about what you do?
- Your dad died...

1383
01:51:38,164 --> 01:51:42,066
saving my life, and these people were killin' firemen for money.

1384
01:51:42,135 --> 01:51:45,627
- Swayzak.
- He killed our friends for money.

1385
01:51:45,705 --> 01:51:47,639
What the fuck would you do?

1386
01:51:47,707 --> 01:51:51,173
You're his lieutenant. You've gotta handle this.

1387
01:51:51,306 --> 01:51:54,469
[Rumbling]

1388
01:51:54,543 --> 01:51:56,477
It's going!

1389
01:51:56,545 --> 01:51:59,639
Get to the side! It's gonna go!

1390
01:52:17,900 --> 01:52:21,165
[Moaning]

1391
01:52:46,495 --> 01:52:50,591
17! Somebody! I'm in the elevator shaft.

1392
01:52:50,666 --> 01:52:52,190
Help me!

1393
01:53:07,015 --> 01:53:10,280
Help, somebody!

1394
01:53:17,793 --> 01:53:21,524
17, help!

1395
01:53:32,307 --> 01:53:35,174
- Brian!
- Stephen!

1396
01:53:35,244 --> 01:53:38,771
I'm burning up in here!

1397
01:53:51,393 --> 01:53:53,861
- You all right?
- Yeah. You all right?

1398
01:53:53,929 --> 01:53:55,920
Uh-huh.

1399
01:53:55,998 --> 01:54:00,059
Come on. We gotta go get him.

1400
01:54:00,135 --> 01:54:03,969
[Stephen] We gotta get outta here. The whole place is goin' up.

1401
01:54:16,818 --> 01:54:20,254
Look out! Come on. This way.

1402
01:54:35,237 --> 01:54:37,569
Wait a minute. Brian!

1403
01:54:38,640 --> 01:54:41,006
Jesus!

1404
01:55:26,054 --> 01:55:29,717
I just couldn't let it go, Bull.

1405
01:55:29,791 --> 01:55:33,352
Yeah.

1406
01:56:02,124 --> 01:56:05,093
- Agh. I got ya.
- [Groaning]

1407
01:56:14,636 --> 01:56:16,866
[Screaming]

1408
01:56:45,901 --> 01:56:48,199
Let me go, Bull.

1409
01:56:49,271 --> 01:56:54,208
You go... we go.

1410
01:56:59,981 --> 01:57:02,779
Stephen!

1411
01:57:06,688 --> 01:57:09,521
Nooo!

1412
01:57:30,612 --> 01:57:32,546
Don't move.

1413
01:57:36,685 --> 01:57:38,653
Don't move, damn it.

1414
01:57:38,720 --> 01:57:41,211
- What?
- Just lie down.

1415
01:57:41,289 --> 01:57:43,780
[Grunting]

1416
01:57:46,428 --> 01:57:48,692
Oh, shit!

1417
01:57:53,568 --> 01:57:56,901
Pengelly, up here!

1418
01:57:56,972 --> 01:58:00,271
Did you hear somebody? Stephen!

1419
01:58:00,342 --> 01:58:03,675
- Pengelly!
- Up here!

1420
01:58:03,745 --> 01:58:05,679
- Where's he at?
- Over there!

1421
01:58:05,747 --> 01:58:07,339
Pengelly!

1422
01:58:09,818 --> 01:58:12,446
We're gonna get you outta here. Lay down. Don't move.

1423
01:58:18,760 --> 01:58:21,092
Get goin'!

1424
01:58:25,801 --> 01:58:28,565
Pengelly, I lost the line.

1425
01:58:35,644 --> 01:58:39,341
[Grunting]

1426
01:58:39,414 --> 01:58:42,247
I'm going for the hose.

1427
01:59:24,793 --> 01:59:26,784
Brian!

1428
01:59:40,577 --> 01:59:43,444
- Go!
- All right, move it!

1429
01:59:50,186 --> 01:59:52,484
Agh!

1430
02:00:05,568 --> 02:00:07,661
Come on.

1431
02:00:23,553 --> 02:00:25,714
Look at him.

1432
02:00:25,788 --> 02:00:28,416
That's my brother, goddamn it.

1433
02:00:34,030 --> 02:00:36,521
Agh!

1434
02:00:36,599 --> 02:00:39,295
[Indistinct Yelling]

1435
02:00:41,237 --> 02:00:43,171
How is he? Is he okay?

1436
02:00:44,440 --> 02:00:49,537
- Let's move it. Let's go.
- Hang on.

1437
02:00:49,612 --> 02:00:51,546
Let's move it, now!

1438
02:00:51,614 --> 02:00:54,447
- Up with him!
- Come on.

1439
02:00:54,517 --> 02:00:59,318
- All right, Bull.
- He's gonna make it.

1440
02:01:07,530 --> 02:01:09,896
I gotta get this collar on. Come on. Help us out.

1441
02:01:09,966 --> 02:01:11,900
I don't want it.

1442
02:01:11,968 --> 02:01:14,903
Brian?

1443
02:01:14,971 --> 02:01:19,965
Don't tell them about Adcox. Don't let them.

1444
02:01:20,043 --> 02:01:23,069
- It'll hurt the department.
- I won't.

1445
02:01:23,146 --> 02:01:28,243
- Monitor on.
- I'm sorry. I thought--

1446
02:01:28,318 --> 02:01:32,516
B.P.: 90 over 60.

1447
02:01:32,589 --> 02:01:34,614
I'm sorry I ever thought you--

1448
02:01:34,691 --> 02:01:38,388
I know.

1449
02:01:43,299 --> 02:01:47,030
- I-- I beat it.
- Blood pressure: 80 over 60.

1450
02:01:47,103 --> 02:01:49,264
The fire never got me.

1451
02:01:49,339 --> 02:01:51,239
Hang in there.

1452
02:01:51,307 --> 02:01:53,366
- [Gasping]
- You're gonna make it!

1453
02:01:53,443 --> 02:01:55,377
[Paramedic] Lidocaine, now!

1454
02:01:55,445 --> 02:01:58,243
- Is he going to be all right?
- He's spiking!

1455
02:02:00,350 --> 02:02:03,183
Who's your brother, Brian?

1456
02:02:05,989 --> 02:02:08,787
You are, Stephen.

1457
02:02:12,996 --> 02:02:16,864
[Paramedic] Lidocaine in.

1458
02:02:21,838 --> 02:02:25,501
I'm tired of hearing the sirens.

1459
02:02:25,575 --> 02:02:30,308
Turn... turn the siren off, Brian.

1460
02:02:31,681 --> 02:02:34,013
Turn the siren off.

1461
02:02:34,083 --> 02:02:36,017
You're gonna be all right, goddamn it!

1462
02:02:36,085 --> 02:02:39,577
Hang in! Let's go! Move this thing.

1463
02:02:39,656 --> 02:02:42,124
Don't you die on me now. You hear me?

1464
02:02:42,191 --> 02:02:44,887
Hang in there. We're almost there.

1465
02:02:44,961 --> 02:02:47,987
It's not your time now. I need you.

1466
02:02:49,799 --> 02:02:53,098
[EKG Beeping Stops]

1467
02:02:53,169 --> 02:02:57,105
You're gonna make it.

1468
02:02:59,175 --> 02:03:02,008
Clear!

1469
02:03:02,078 --> 02:03:06,538
Starting compression. One, two, three, four, five.

1470
02:03:07,917 --> 02:03:11,216
One, two, three, four, five.

1471
02:03:11,287 --> 02:03:16,088
One, two, three, four, five.

1472
02:03:16,159 --> 02:03:18,320
One, two--

1473
02:03:24,400 --> 02:03:28,700
# [Bagpipes]

1474
02:05:00,363 --> 02:05:03,196
[Rimgale] In the Chicago fire department...

1475
02:05:03,266 --> 02:05:05,461
the alarm code 3-3-5 signifies...

1476
02:05:05,535 --> 02:05:08,868
that the company has returned home to quarters.

1477
02:05:08,938 --> 02:05:12,499
We will now ring out that code to welcome home...

1478
02:05:12,575 --> 02:05:17,342
Firefighter John Adcox and Lieutenant Stephen McCaffrey.

1479
02:05:17,413 --> 02:05:20,507
[Ding, Ding, Ding]

1480
02:05:22,218 --> 02:05:25,278
[Ding, Ding, Ding]

1481
02:05:26,956 --> 02:05:33,259
[Ding, Ding, Ding, Ding, Ding]

1482
02:05:43,906 --> 02:05:47,205
Honor guard, hand salute!

1483
02:05:53,049 --> 02:05:57,611
Honor guard, dismissed!

1484
02:06:19,575 --> 02:06:21,702
Gentlemen, can we help you?

1485
02:06:21,777 --> 02:06:25,543
Police. We have a subpoena for Alderman Swayzak.

1486
02:06:25,615 --> 02:06:28,584
- Ah, Inspector--
- Alderman Swayzak, how are you doin'?

1487
02:06:28,651 --> 02:06:33,179
- This will only take a minute.
- I'm in a press conference.

1488
02:06:33,256 --> 02:06:36,384
These detectives would like to question you why you secretly paid...

1489
02:06:36,459 --> 02:06:38,859
Donald Cosgrove, Jeffrey Holcomb, and Alan Seagrave...

1490
02:06:38,928 --> 02:06:41,362
to create a phony manpower study.

1491
02:06:41,430 --> 02:06:45,992
[Rimgale] Ask him who made money off firemen dying.

1492
02:06:50,940 --> 02:06:54,569
You see that glow flashing in the corner of your eye?

1493
02:06:54,644 --> 02:06:57,238
That's your career dissipation light.

1494
02:06:57,313 --> 02:07:00,282
It just went into high gear.

1495
02:07:03,619 --> 02:07:06,611
I'll have my aides look into it as soon as they can. Thank you.

1496
02:07:06,689 --> 02:07:10,750
Mr. Alderman has no further comment. This conference is over.

1497
02:07:30,846 --> 02:07:33,280
[Fire Bell]

1498
02:07:33,349 --> 02:07:37,581
[Dispatcher] ...1718 West Maplewood.

1499
02:07:37,653 --> 02:07:41,350
1718 West Maplewood. Got it, Cap?

1500
02:07:43,092 --> 02:07:46,255
Okay, into the truck. Code 32.

1501
02:07:48,464 --> 02:07:50,398
Nightengale!

1502
02:08:08,951 --> 02:08:11,078
We're gonna be damn busy.

1503
02:08:11,687 --> 02:08:13,621
Salsa!

1504
02:08:24,266 --> 02:08:26,700
[Horn Blast]

1505
02:08:26,769 --> 02:08:29,203
[Siren]

1506
02:08:45,921 --> 02:08:49,152
You're doin' it wrong!

1507
02:08:59,268 --> 02:09:01,828
Thanks.

1508
02:09:01,904 --> 02:09:04,304
All right.

1509
02:10:31,576 --> 02:10:35,512
# ["Set Me ln Motion" performed by Bruce Hornsby]

1510
02:10:42,821 --> 02:10:47,383
#You sit there with a blank expression#

1511
02:10:47,459 --> 02:10:52,522
#Say you can't go on anymore#

1512
02:10:52,597 --> 02:10:57,466
#It's not like me to come out and help you#

1513
02:10:57,535 --> 02:11:02,871
#Maybe I've been down this road before#

1514
02:11:02,941 --> 02:11:05,671
#Been livin' in the shadows#

1515
02:11:05,743 --> 02:11:08,007
#Now you come out slow#

